{"term": "1967", "caseName": "Bloom v. Illinois", "caseLink": "https://www.oyez.org/cases/1967/52", "caseTranscripts": [{"transcriptTitle": "Oral Argument - January 16, 1968", "transcriptLink": "https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren15/oral_argument_audio/15407", "transcript": [{"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Number 52, S.Edward Bloom versus Illinois.", "start": 0, "stop": 26.991, "duration": 26.99, "cleanText": [["number", "sedward", "bloom", "versus", "illinois"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Eben.", "start": 26.991, "stop": 28.741, "duration": 1.75, "cleanText": [["mr", "eben"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you Your Honor.", "start": 28.741, "stop": 31.972, "duration": 3.23, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, associate justices, may it please the court.", "start": 31.972, "stop": 39.78, "duration": 7.81, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "associate", "justice", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "Each time that I have the pleasure of appearing before this Court, I have taken the liberty at the outset of calling the attention of the Court to the fact that I am somewhat hard of hearing.", "start": 39.78, "stop": 53.51, "duration": 13.73, "cleanText": [["each", "time", "that", "i", "have", "the", "pleasure", "of", "appear", "before", "this", "court", "i", "have", "take", "the", "liberty", "at", "the", "outset", "of", "call", "the", "attention", "of", "the", "court", "to", "the", "fact", "that", "i", "be", "somewhat", "hard", "of", "hearing"]]}, {"text": "And each time in the past when I have done that Mr. Justice Frankfurter invariably would ask me whether or not I made that statement in order to avoid having the Court ask me any questions and each time, I always replied to Mr. Justice Frankfurter that I'm welcome to questions and that I only make the statement to the end that the Court will bear with me a little if I do not seem to -- at first, to hear what you have to say to me.", "start": 53.51, "stop": 82.712, "duration": 29.2, "cleanText": [["and", "each", "time", "in", "the", "past", "when", "i", "have", "do", "that", "mr", "justice", "frankfurter", "invariably", "would", "ask", "me", "whether", "or", "not", "i", "make", "that", "statement", "in", "order", "to", "avoid", "have", "the", "court", "ask", "me", "any", "question", "and", "each", "time", "i", "always", "reply", "to", "mr", "justice", "frankfurter", "that", "I", "be", "welcome", "to", "question", "and", "that", "i", "only", "make", "the", "statement", "to", "the", "end", "that", "the", "court", "will", "bear", "with", "me", "a", "little", "if", "i", "do", "not", "seem", "to", "at", "first", "to", "hear", "what", "you", "have", "to", "say", "to", "me"]]}, {"text": "This case Your Honors again, brings to this Court the troublesome question and I say troublesome because it has bothered the Court in the past on three separate occasions.", "start": 82.712, "stop": 98.162, "duration": 15.45, "cleanText": [["this", "case", "your", "honor", "again", "bring", "to", "this", "court", "the", "troublesome", "question", "and", "i", "say", "troublesome", "because", "it", "have", "bother", "the", "court", "in", "the", "past", "on", "three", "separate", "occasion"]]}, {"text": "The question deals with the right to a trial by jury in a criminal contempt case.", "start": 98.162, "stop": 105.327, "duration": 7.16, "cleanText": [["the", "question", "deal", "with", "the", "right", "to", "a", "trial", "by", "jury", "in", "a", "criminal", "contempt", "case"]]}, {"text": "As the Court will recall, this matter has come before Your Honors in the past as recently as in Cheff v. Schnackenberg, and prior to that in the Barnett case and prior to that in the Green case.", "start": 105.327, "stop": 122.091, "duration": 16.76, "cleanText": [["as", "the", "court", "will", "recall", "this", "matter", "have", "come", "before", "your", "honor", "in", "the", "past", "as", "recently", "as", "in", "cheff", "v", "schnackenberg", "and", "prior", "to", "that", "in", "the", "barnett", "case", "and", "prior", "to", "that", "in", "the", "green", "case"]]}, {"text": "In every instance, the Court has split one way or another and have stated their diverge views with great strength.", "start": 122.091, "stop": 132.971, "duration": 10.88, "cleanText": [["in", "every", "instance", "the", "court", "have", "split", "one", "way", "or", "another", "and", "have", "state", "their", "diverge", "view", "with", "great", "strength"]]}, {"text": "The matter actually comes here now upon the grant of a writ of certiorari to the Supreme Court of the State of Illinois to review a judgment by that court which affirmed a judgment added in the probate court of Cook County against the petitioner who was charged with criminal contempt of that court.", "start": 132.971, "stop": 160.065, "duration": 27.09, "cleanText": [["the", "matter", "actually", "come", "here", "now", "upon", "the", "grant", "of", "a", "writ", "of", "certiorari", "to", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "the", "state", "of", "illinois", "to", "review", "a", "judgment", "by", "that", "court", "which", "affirm", "a", "judgment", "add", "in", "the", "probate", "court", "of", "cook", "county", "against", "the", "petitioner", "who", "be", "charge", "with", "criminal", "contempt", "of", "that", "court"]]}, {"text": "Now the conduct upon which the petitioner was brought to trial in that court related to his alleged filing in the Court of a spurious will, a will alleged in the pleadings to have been prepared by the petitioner subsequent to the death of the decedent.", "start": 160.065, "stop": 181.568, "duration": 21.5, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "conduct", "upon", "which", "the", "petitioner", "be", "bring", "to", "trial", "in", "that", "court", "relate", "to", "his", "alleged", "filing", "in", "the", "court", "of", "a", "spurious", "will", "a", "will", "allege", "in", "the", "pleading", "to", "have", "be", "prepare", "by", "the", "petitioner", "subsequent", "to", "the", "death", "of", "the", "decedent"]]}, {"text": "The petitioner is a member of the Bar of the State of Illinois actually.", "start": 181.568, "stop": 191.982, "duration": 10.41, "cleanText": [["the", "petitioner", "be", "a", "member", "of", "the", "bar", "of", "the", "state", "of", "illinois", "actually"]]}, {"text": "In the pleading, it is said that he prepared this in his office with the aid of his stenographer that thereafter he procured witnesses who signed it after the death of the decedent that he then filed the will with the clerk, with probate court and that he then presented it for admission.", "start": 191.982, "stop": 215.245, "duration": 23.26, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "pleading", "it", "be", "say", "that", "he", "prepare", "this", "in", "his", "office", "with", "the", "aid", "of", "his", "stenographer", "that", "thereafter", "he", "procure", "witness", "who", "sign", "it", "after", "the", "death", "of", "the", "decedent", "that", "he", "then", "file", "the", "will", "with", "the", "clerk", "with", "probate", "court", "and", "that", "he", "then", "present", "it", "for", "admission"]]}, {"text": "When the case came on for trial, we asked for a jury.", "start": 215.245, "stop": 221.053, "duration": 5.81, "cleanText": [["when", "the", "case", "come", "on", "for", "trial", "we", "ask", "for", "a", "jury"]]}, {"text": "Our request for a jury was timely at the Illinois law.", "start": 221.053, "stop": 225.649, "duration": 4.6, "cleanText": [["our", "request", "for", "a", "jury", "be", "timely", "at", "the", "illinois", "law"]]}, {"text": "The trial judge saw fit to deny that request and the trial was then entered upon and consumed approximately 10 days.", "start": 225.649, "stop": 236.03, "duration": 10.38, "cleanText": [["the", "trial", "judge", "saw", "fit", "to", "deny", "that", "request", "and", "the", "trial", "be", "then", "enter", "upon", "and", "consume", "approximately", "day"]]}, {"text": "At the conclusion of the trial, the petitioner was found guilty of all of those matters which I have already described to the Court.", "start": 236.03, "stop": 245.814, "duration": 9.78, "cleanText": [["at", "the", "conclusion", "of", "the", "trial", "the", "petitioner", "be", "find", "guilty", "of", "all", "of", "those", "matter", "which", "i", "have", "already", "describe", "to", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "And the order recited that he was in delegation of the dignity of the Court and of the orderly processes of the Court.", "start": 245.814, "stop": 256.908, "duration": 11.09, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "order", "recite", "that", "he", "be", "in", "delegation", "of", "the", "dignity", "of", "the", "court", "and", "of", "the", "orderly", "process", "of", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "Also during the trial, a fact issue was raised as to the guilt or innocence of petitioner.", "start": 256.908, "stop": 266.884, "duration": 9.98, "cleanText": [["also", "during", "the", "trial", "a", "fact", "issue", "be", "raise", "as", "to", "the", "guilt", "or", "innocence", "of", "petitioner"]]}, {"text": "That fact issue was raised by the testimony of a psychiatrist who testified that a part of his examination of petitioner and upon a hypothetical question that the petitioner could not possibly have possessed the benevolent intent which is necessary at the State of Illinois to support a charge of criminal contempt.", "start": 266.884, "stop": 296.029, "duration": 29.14, "cleanText": [["that", "fact", "issue", "be", "raise", "by", "the", "testimony", "of", "a", "psychiatrist", "who", "testify", "that", "a", "part", "of", "his", "examination", "of", "petitioner", "and", "upon", "a", "hypothetical", "question", "that", "the", "petitioner", "could", "not", "possibly", "have", "possess", "the", "benevolent", "intent", "which", "be", "necessary", "at", "the", "state", "of", "illinois", "to", "support", "a", "charge", "of", "criminal", "contempt"]]}, {"text": "The portion of this case which makes it somewhat different than the cases which have come to the Court's attention in the past lies in the fact here that the conduct complaint of as pleaded in the petition constitutes a felony under the criminal code of the State of Illinois of 1961.", "start": 296.029, "stop": 322.254, "duration": 26.23, "cleanText": [["the", "portion", "of", "this", "case", "which", "make", "it", "somewhat", "different", "than", "the", "case", "which", "have", "come", "to", "the", "court", "s", "attention", "in", "the", "past", "lie", "in", "the", "fact", "here", "that", "the", "conduct", "complaint", "of", "as", "plead", "in", "the", "petition", "constitute", "a", "felony", "under", "the", "criminal", "code", "of", "the", "state", "of", "illinois", "of"]]}, {"text": "It constitutes a felony under the provisions of Section 17-3 of that code which to deals with forgery and makes it a felony punishable by a sentence of one to 14 years for one who utters knowingly a forged document.", "start": 322.254, "stop": 341.396, "duration": 19.14, "cleanText": [["it", "constitute", "a", "felony", "under", "the", "provision", "of", "section", "of", "that", "code", "which", "to", "deal", "with", "forgery", "and", "make", "it", "a", "felony", "punishable", "by", "a", "sentence", "of", "one", "to", "year", "for", "one", "who", "utter", "knowingly", "a", "forged", "document"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "What was the punishment here?", "start": 341.396, "stop": 343.264, "duration": 1.87, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "the", "punishment", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm sorry, what?", "start": 343.264, "stop": 343.856, "duration": 0.59, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sorry", "what"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "What was the punishment here?", "start": 343.856, "stop": 346.453, "duration": 2.6, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "the", "punishment", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "The petitioner was sentenced to two years in the common jail of Cook County and is presently at large on bail pending his appeal to the Illinois Supreme Court and then the grant of certiorari here.", "start": 346.453, "stop": 361.886, "duration": 15.43, "cleanText": [["the", "petitioner", "be", "sentence", "to", "two", "year", "in", "the", "common", "jail", "of", "cook", "county", "and", "be", "presently", "at", "large", "on", "bail", "pending", "his", "appeal", "to", "the", "illinois", "supreme", "court", "and", "then", "the", "grant", "of", "certiorari", "here"]]}, {"text": "Now, the case also presents two other constitutional questions which I hope to come to later because I would like to have the main impact of my argument centered on the question of the right to trial by jury in this type of case.", "start": 361.886, "stop": 380.096, "duration": 18.21, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "case", "also", "present", "two", "other", "constitutional", "question", "which", "i", "hope", "to", "come", "to", "later", "because", "i", "would", "like", "to", "have", "the", "main", "impact", "of", "my", "argument", "center", "on", "the", "question", "of", "the", "right", "to", "trial", "by", "jury", "in", "this", "type", "of", "case"]]}, {"text": "But at passing, so that it will come as no surprise to the Court, we also alleged that the trial judge had a secret report furnished him by an amicus curiae who was appointed by him and that this report was only made limitedly available to us at the trial and not at its entirety.", "start": 380.096, "stop": 403.125, "duration": 23.03, "cleanText": [["but", "at", "passing", "so", "that", "it", "will", "come", "as", "no", "surprise", "to", "the", "court", "we", "also", "allege", "that", "the", "trial", "judge", "have", "a", "secret", "report", "furnish", "him", "by", "an", "amicus", "curia", "who", "be", "appoint", "by", "him", "and", "that", "this", "report", "be", "only", "make", "limitedly", "available", "to", "us", "at", "the", "trial", "and", "not", "at", "its", "entirety"]]}, {"text": "And the third constitutional point deals with the question of a comment by the prosecutor at the conclusion of the summary that the petitioner in that case have failed to take the stand.", "start": 403.125, "stop": 419.599, "duration": 16.47, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "third", "constitutional", "point", "deal", "with", "the", "question", "of", "a", "comment", "by", "the", "prosecutor", "at", "the", "conclusion", "of", "the", "summary", "that", "the", "petitioner", "in", "that", "case", "have", "fail", "to", "take", "the", "stand"]]}, {"text": "I do not wish to take up the time of this Court needlessly to explain to the Court that which I know it already knows.", "start": 419.599, "stop": 431.816, "duration": 12.22, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "wish", "to", "take", "up", "the", "time", "of", "this", "court", "needlessly", "to", "explain", "to", "the", "court", "that", "which", "i", "know", "it", "already", "know"]]}, {"text": "I am sure that this Court is much more familiar with the dissent of Mr. Justice Black.", "start": 431.816, "stop": 439.424, "duration": 7.61, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "sure", "that", "this", "court", "be", "much", "more", "familiar", "with", "the", "dissent", "of", "mr", "justice", "black"]]}, {"text": "In fact, the number of dissent of Mr. Justice Black in this field and his presentation of all of the reasons why upon a consideration of ancient law, Magna Carta, the statutes prevailing in the 13 colonies.", "start": 439.424, "stop": 458.447, "duration": 19.02, "cleanText": [["in", "fact", "the", "number", "of", "dissent", "of", "mr", "justice", "black", "in", "this", "field", "and", "his", "presentation", "of", "all", "of", "the", "reason", "why", "upon", "a", "consideration", "of", "ancient", "law", "magna", "carta", "the", "statute", "prevail", "in", "the", "colony"]]}, {"text": "A review of ancient common law English decisions and so on.", "start": 458.447, "stop": 464.853, "duration": 6.41, "cleanText": [["a", "review", "of", "ancient", "common", "law", "english", "decision", "and", "so", "on"]]}, {"text": "Why he stands for the proposition that there is just no reason in logic why a criminal contempt of any sort should be treated any differently than a crime or a criminal prosecution and therefore subject to Article III, Section 2 of the constitution as well as the Sixth Amendment of the constitution.", "start": 464.853, "stop": 491.79, "duration": 26.94, "cleanText": [["why", "he", "stand", "for", "the", "proposition", "that", "there", "be", "just", "no", "reason", "in", "logic", "why", "a", "criminal", "contempt", "of", "any", "sort", "should", "be", "treat", "any", "differently", "than", "a", "crime", "or", "a", "criminal", "prosecution", "and", "therefore", "subject", "to", "article", "iii", "section", "of", "the", "constitution", "as", "well", "as", "the", "sixth", "amendment", "of", "the", "constitution"]]}, {"text": "Elegant treatment has been given to the same subject by Mr. Justice Goldberg in his dissent in the Barnett case and Mr. Justice Douglas from time to time has made references in dissents to this.", "start": 491.79, "stop": 507.618, "duration": 15.83, "cleanText": [["elegant", "treatment", "have", "be", "give", "to", "the", "same", "subject", "by", "mr", "justice", "goldberg", "in", "his", "dissent", "in", "the", "barnett", "case", "and", "mr", "justice", "douglas", "from", "time", "to", "time", "have", "make", "reference", "in", "dissent", "to", "this"]]}, {"text": "On the other hand as the Court knows Mr. Justice Harlan has consistently taken a position in opposition to the theory which we now propose.", "start": 507.618, "stop": 519.051, "duration": 11.43, "cleanText": [["on", "the", "other", "hand", "as", "the", "court", "know", "mr", "justice", "harlan", "have", "consistently", "take", "a", "position", "in", "opposition", "to", "the", "theory", "which", "we", "now", "propose"]]}, {"text": "But I thought that the basis for Mr. Justice Harlan's opinions in the past is somewhat -- maybe distinguished here since in Green and in Barnett the two cases prior to Cheff, there was never any question of the conduct complained off in those cases constituting a felony as this particular conduct does here.", "start": 519.051, "stop": 550.708, "duration": 31.66, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "think", "that", "the", "basis", "for", "mr", "justice", "harlan", "s", "opinion", "in", "the", "past", "be", "somewhat", "maybe", "distinguish", "here", "since", "in", "green", "and", "in", "barnett", "the", "two", "case", "prior", "to", "cheff", "there", "be", "never", "any", "question", "of", "the", "conduct", "complain", "off", "in", "those", "case", "constitute", "a", "felony", "as", "this", "particular", "conduct", "do", "here"]]}, {"text": "As of felony of course, the petitioner might well have been indicted by a grand jury on which event at the Illinois law and under the Illinois constitution, it would have been entitled to a trial by jury.", "start": 550.708, "stop": 562.847, "duration": 12.14, "cleanText": [["as", "of", "felony", "of", "course", "the", "petitioner", "might", "well", "have", "be", "indict", "by", "a", "grand", "jury", "on", "which", "event", "at", "the", "illinois", "law", "and", "under", "the", "illinois", "constitution", "it", "would", "have", "be", "entitle", "to", "a", "trial", "by", "jury"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, wasn't there a statute in Green?", "start": 562.847, "stop": 564.967, "duration": 2.12, "cleanText": [["well", "be", "not", "there", "a", "statute", "in", "green"]]}, {"text": "And I thought there was a statute in Green and it was one year penalty but the Court gave him five years for contempt, am I wrong in that?", "start": 564.967, "stop": 576.403, "duration": 11.44, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "thought", "there", "be", "a", "statute", "in", "green", "and", "it", "be", "one", "year", "penalty", "but", "the", "court", "give", "him", "five", "year", "for", "contempt", "be", "i", "wrong", "in", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "In Green as I recall the facts Your Honor, the -- there had been jumping of bail and you're quite right.", "start": 576.403, "stop": 583.246, "duration": 6.84, "cleanText": [["in", "green", "as", "i", "recall", "the", "fact", "your", "honor", "the", "there", "have", "be", "jump", "of", "bail", "and", "you", "be", "quite", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Voice Overlap)", "start": 583.246, "stop": 584.492, "duration": 1.25, "cleanText": [["voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "And there was a one year penalty in connection with that.", "start": 584.492, "stop": 587.293, "duration": 2.8, "cleanText": [["and", "there", "be", "a", "one", "year", "penalty", "in", "connection", "with", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 587.293, "stop": 587.652, "duration": 0.36, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "But that of course was not a felony.", "start": 587.652, "stop": 589.036, "duration": 1.38, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "of", "course", "be", "not", "a", "felony"]]}, {"text": "That would be at least a misdemeanor if the penalty is only one year.", "start": 589.036, "stop": 591.76, "duration": 2.72, "cleanText": [["that", "would", "be", "at", "least", "a", "misdemeanor", "if", "the", "penalty", "be", "only", "one", "year"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "That was the subject of the contempt also that he had jumped his bail and did not report it.", "start": 591.76, "stop": 597.065, "duration": 5.31, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "subject", "of", "the", "contempt", "also", "that", "he", "have", "jump", "his", "bail", "and", "do", "not", "report", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, he jumped there then they were brought back and then --", "start": 597.065, "stop": 599.199, "duration": 2.13, "cleanText": [["yes", "he", "jump", "there", "then", "they", "we", "be", "bring", "back", "and", "then"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 599.199, "stop": 599.203, "duration": 0, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- given him five years on the contempt charge.", "start": 599.203, "stop": 601.065, "duration": 1.86, "cleanText": [["give", "him", "five", "year", "on", "the", "contempt", "charge"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 601.065, "stop": 601.477, "duration": 0.41, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's quite correct.", "start": 601.477, "stop": 603.66, "duration": 2.18, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "quite", "correct"]]}, {"text": "Now it seems to me that.", "start": 603.66, "stop": 606.277, "duration": 2.62, "cleanText": [["now", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "I may be wrong if my recollection of it is --", "start": 606.277, "stop": 609.442, "duration": 3.16, "cleanText": [["i", "may", "be", "wrong", "if", "my", "recollection", "of", "it", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm sorry Mr.  Justice Harlan.", "start": 609.442, "stop": 610.656, "duration": 1.21, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sorry", "mr", "justice", "harlan"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "I say, \"I may be wrong but my recollection of it is that there was a bit of jump of the statute in Green but the sentence provided for was wrong with its intentions.", "start": 610.656, "stop": 620.835, "duration": 10.18, "cleanText": [["i", "say", "i", "may", "be", "wrong", "but", "my", "recollection", "of", "it", "be", "that", "there", "be", "a", "bit", "of", "jump", "of", "the", "statute", "in", "green", "but", "the", "sentence", "provide", "for", "be", "wrong", "with", "its", "intention"]]}, {"text": "I may be wrong about --", "start": 620.835, "stop": 622.277, "duration": 1.44, "cleanText": [["i", "may", "be", "wrong", "about"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, that's what I understood the Chief Justice to say.", "start": 622.277, "stop": 624.899, "duration": 2.62, "cleanText": [["yes", "that", "be", "what", "i", "understand", "the", "chief", "justice", "to", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 624.899, "stop": 625.377, "duration": 0.48, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "And I concede that there was such a statute.", "start": 625.377, "stop": 627.864, "duration": 2.49, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "concede", "that", "there", "be", "such", "a", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "I thought it was a five-year sentence.", "start": 627.864, "stop": 635.09, "duration": 7.23, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "be", "a", "five", "year", "sentence"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "In Cheff, which was the last time these troubles and problem came here, six of the justices seemed for one reason or another to be on the side which I now proposed.", "start": 635.09, "stop": 652.424, "duration": 17.33, "cleanText": [["in", "cheff", "which", "be", "the", "last", "time", "these", "trouble", "and", "problem", "come", "here", "six", "of", "the", "justice", "seem", "for", "one", "reason", "or", "another", "to", "be", "on", "the", "side", "which", "i", "now", "propose"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Justice Black and Mr. Justice Douglas quite consistently adhered to their prior dissents.", "start": 652.424, "stop": 660.789, "duration": 8.37, "cleanText": [["mr", "justice", "black", "and", "mr", "justice", "douglas", "quite", "consistently", "adhere", "to", "their", "prior", "dissent"]]}, {"text": "Four other justices, however, consisting of the Chief Justice I believe, Mr. Justice Brennan and Mr. Justice Fortas as I recall took the position that where or rather they equate and I should say, a criminal contempt to a petty crime and then taking the petty crime which is defined under the appropriate United States statute, I believe it's 18 U.S.C 1.", "start": 660.789, "stop": 695.569, "duration": 34.78, "cleanText": [["four", "other", "justice", "however", "consist", "of", "the", "chief", "justice", "i", "believe", "mr", "justice", "brennan", "and", "mr", "justice", "fortas", "as", "i", "recall", "take", "the", "position", "that", "where", "or", "rather", "they", "equate", "and", "i", "should", "say", "a", "criminal", "contempt", "to", "a", "petty", "crime", "and", "then", "take", "the", "petty", "crime", "which", "be", "define", "under", "the", "appropriate", "united", "state", "statute", "i", "believe", "it", "be", "usc"]]}, {"text": "I found there that the maximum penalty to constitute a petty crime was six months and concluding that upon the equation which I just mentioned that therefore it is constitutionally possible to impose a sentence in a case where a disobedience of the Court order was involved which did not exceed six months.", "start": 695.569, "stop": 721.16, "duration": 25.59, "cleanText": [["i", "find", "there", "that", "the", "maximum", "penalty", "to", "constitute", "a", "petty", "crime", "be", "six", "month", "and", "conclude", "that", "upon", "the", "equation", "which", "i", "just", "mention", "that", "therefore", "it", "be", "constitutionally", "possible", "to", "impose", "a", "sentence", "in", "a", "case", "where", "a", "disobedience", "of", "the", "court", "order", "be", "involve", "which", "do", "not", "exceed", "six", "month"]]}, {"text": "But nevertheless, a caveat was published to the lower courts which in the language of this Court seem to indicate that lower courts could not sentence to more than six months in a criminal contempt case.", "start": 721.16, "stop": 742.31, "duration": 21.15, "cleanText": [["but", "nevertheless", "a", "caveat", "be", "publish", "to", "the", "low", "court", "which", "in", "the", "language", "of", "this", "court", "seem", "to", "indicate", "that", "low", "court", "could", "not", "sentence", "to", "more", "than", "six", "month", "in", "a", "criminal", "contempt", "case"]]}, {"text": "And if they intended to sentence for a longer period of time then a jury trial was required.", "start": 742.31, "stop": 750.927, "duration": 8.62, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "they", "intend", "to", "sentence", "for", "a", "long", "period", "of", "time", "then", "a", "jury", "trial", "be", "require"]]}, {"text": "My distinguished adversaries from the State of Illinois take the position that this is not a constitutional finding by this Court and was merely an exercise of the supervisory powers of the Court.", "start": 750.927, "stop": 767.587, "duration": 16.66, "cleanText": [["my", "distinguished", "adversary", "from", "the", "state", "of", "illinois", "take", "the", "position", "that", "this", "be", "not", "a", "constitutional", "finding", "by", "this", "court", "and", "be", "merely", "an", "exercise", "of", "the", "supervisory", "power", "of", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "I of course contend the opposite and I say that it would have been impossible for this Court no matter what it called it to have decided the question presented in Cheff without as a matter of logic deciding when the issue of this caveat that any punishment more than six months was unconstitutional under the Sixth Amendment and Article III.", "start": 767.587, "stop": 792.153, "duration": 24.57, "cleanText": [["i", "of", "course", "contend", "the", "opposite", "and", "i", "say", "that", "it", "would", "have", "be", "impossible", "for", "this", "court", "no", "matter", "what", "it", "call", "it", "to", "have", "decide", "the", "question", "present", "in", "cheff", "without", "as", "a", "matter", "of", "logic", "decide", "when", "the", "issue", "of", "this", "caveat", "that", "any", "punishment", "more", "than", "six", "month", "be", "unconstitutional", "under", "the", "sixth", "amendment", "and", "article", "iii"]]}, {"text": "We have briefed this fully as has the state.", "start": 792.153, "stop": 795.654, "duration": 3.5, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "brief", "this", "fully", "as", "have", "the", "state"]]}, {"text": "Now then, it seems also to me as a matter of reasoning that there is just no reason whatsoever why a criminal contempt should ever be considered in any manner different from the ordinary crime or criminal prosecution.", "start": 795.654, "stop": 819.76, "duration": 24.11, "cleanText": [["now", "then", "it", "seem", "also", "to", "me", "as", "a", "matter", "of", "reason", "that", "there", "be", "just", "no", "reason", "whatsoever", "why", "a", "criminal", "contempt", "should", "ever", "be", "consider", "in", "any", "manner", "different", "from", "the", "ordinary", "crime", "or", "criminal", "prosecution"]]}, {"text": "For instance, in the past, this Court as well as the Supreme Court of the State of Illinois had held that a -- an alleged contemnor is entitled to any number of rights all of which are granted to him only in the event of the commission of a crime.", "start": 819.76, "stop": 839.163, "duration": 19.4, "cleanText": [["for", "instance", "in", "the", "past", "this", "court", "as", "well", "as", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "the", "state", "of", "illinois", "have", "hold", "that", "a", "an", "allege", "contemnor", "be", "entitle", "to", "any", "number", "of", "right", "all", "of", "which", "be", "grant", "to", "him", "only", "in", "the", "event", "of", "the", "commission", "of", "a", "crime"]]}, {"text": "For instance, under decisions here and under decisions of the State of Illinois an alleged contemnor is entitled to the presumption of innocence.", "start": 839.163, "stop": 848.484, "duration": 9.32, "cleanText": [["for", "instance", "under", "decision", "here", "and", "under", "decision", "of", "the", "state", "of", "illinois", "an", "allege", "contemnor", "be", "entitle", "to", "the", "presumption", "of", "innocence"]]}, {"text": "He is entitled to the application of the rule that he must be proved guilty beyond all reasonable doubt, self incrimination is not permitted.", "start": 848.484, "stop": 860.389, "duration": 11.9, "cleanText": [["he", "be", "entitle", "to", "the", "application", "of", "the", "rule", "that", "he", "must", "be", "prove", "guilty", "beyond", "all", "reasonable", "doubt", "self", "incrimination", "be", "not", "permit"]]}, {"text": "He has a right to counsel, he has an opportunity to prepare for trial, he must be given notices of the charges against him, he has a right to an impartial arbiter of the facts, he has the benefit of statutes of limitations covering crimes and finally under these decisions, he has the right to petition for pardon.", "start": 860.389, "stop": 884.491, "duration": 24.1, "cleanText": [["he", "have", "a", "right", "to", "counsel", "he", "have", "an", "opportunity", "to", "prepare", "for", "trial", "he", "must", "be", "give", "notice", "of", "the", "charge", "against", "him", "he", "have", "a", "right", "to", "an", "impartial", "arbiter", "of", "the", "fact", "he", "have", "the", "benefit", "of", "statute", "of", "limitation", "cover", "crime", "and", "finally", "under", "these", "decision", "he", "have", "the", "right", "to", "petition", "for", "pardon"]]}, {"text": "It seems to me that there is just no logic to support the theory that a criminal prosecution at any way differs from a crime and more importantly because I do not wish to overstate my own case, more importantly where the conduct charge actually does as it is here does constitute a crime.", "start": 884.491, "stop": 912.477, "duration": 27.99, "cleanText": [["it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "there", "be", "just", "no", "logic", "to", "support", "the", "theory", "that", "a", "criminal", "prosecution", "at", "any", "way", "differs", "from", "a", "crime", "and", "more", "importantly", "because", "i", "do", "not", "wish", "to", "overstate", "my", "own", "case", "more", "importantly", "where", "the", "conduct", "charge", "actually", "do", "as", "it", "be", "here", "do", "constitute", "a", "crime"]]}, {"text": "Now, there is another reason which seems to me logically to support our position and that is by an analysis which I will make very briefly of why a court has a contempt power at all.", "start": 912.477, "stop": 927.922, "duration": 15.45, "cleanText": [["now", "there", "be", "another", "reason", "which", "seem", "to", "me", "logically", "to", "support", "our", "position", "and", "that", "be", "by", "an", "analysis", "which", "i", "will", "make", "very", "briefly", "of", "why", "a", "court", "have", "a", "contempt", "power", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "And there are decisions after decisions saying that courts have this power in order to protect themselves.", "start": 927.922, "stop": 936.487, "duration": 8.56, "cleanText": [["and", "there", "be", "decision", "after", "decision", "say", "that", "court", "have", "this", "power", "in", "order", "to", "protect", "themselves"]]}, {"text": "That is to protect themselves from insult and contumacy committed in their presence or to enforce their judgments and so on.", "start": 936.487, "stop": 945.705, "duration": 9.22, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "to", "protect", "themselves", "from", "insult", "and", "contumacy", "commit", "in", "their", "presence", "or", "to", "enforce", "their", "judgment", "and", "so", "on"]]}, {"text": "But at the same time, the decisions of this Court and particularly the early decisions that indicate that the power of contempt as they said should be the least power adequate to the end proposed.", "start": 945.705, "stop": 961.107, "duration": 15.4, "cleanText": [["but", "at", "the", "same", "time", "the", "decision", "of", "this", "court", "and", "particularly", "the", "early", "decision", "that", "indicate", "that", "the", "power", "of", "contempt", "as", "they", "say", "should", "be", "the", "least", "power", "adequate", "to", "the", "end", "propose"]]}, {"text": "I believe that was in a very early decision of this Court to this case, the Bessette case.", "start": 961.107, "stop": 965.31, "duration": 4.2, "cleanText": [["i", "believe", "that", "be", "in", "a", "very", "early", "decision", "of", "this", "court", "to", "this", "case", "the", "bessette", "case"]]}, {"text": "And so, I point out to the Court that the power -- the contempt power should be used sparingly and in my humble opinion only where it is necessary and under the fact situation as it is in the case at bar, the exercise of the contempt power is not necessary at all.", "start": 965.31, "stop": 986.374, "duration": 21.06, "cleanText": [["and", "so", "i", "point", "out", "to", "the", "court", "that", "the", "power", "the", "contempt", "power", "should", "be", "use", "sparingly", "and", "in", "my", "humble", "opinion", "only", "where", "it", "be", "necessary", "and", "under", "the", "fact", "situation", "as", "it", "be", "in", "the", "case", "at", "bar", "the", "exercise", "of", "the", "contempt", "power", "be", "not", "necessary", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "That is by a court.", "start": 986.374, "stop": 988.109, "duration": 1.74, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "by", "a", "court"]]}, {"text": "Since the Court is given adequate protection by the state's attorney of Cook County in this particular instance who may proceed upon the criminal conduct and bring the man to trial which as I have said before would entitle him to a jury.", "start": 988.109, "stop": 1006.634, "duration": 18.52, "cleanText": [["since", "the", "court", "be", "give", "adequate", "protection", "by", "the", "state", "s", "attorney", "of", "cook", "county", "in", "this", "particular", "instance", "who", "may", "proceed", "upon", "the", "criminal", "conduct", "and", "bring", "the", "man", "to", "trial", "which", "as", "i", "have", "say", "before", "would", "entitle", "him", "to", "a", "jury"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Eben, what would you say about the --", "start": 1006.634, "stop": 1009.525, "duration": 2.89, "cleanText": [["mr", "eben", "what", "would", "you", "say", "about", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Sorry.", "start": 1009.525, "stop": 1009.865, "duration": 0.34, "cleanText": [["sorry"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "What would you say about the case where the conduct is constituting the contempt as criminal under state law or even a felony but the state statute -- the state has a statute limiting the penalty in contempt to say 10 days in jail and $100.00 fine.", "start": 1009.865, "stop": 1031.471, "duration": 21.61, "cleanText": [["what", "would", "you", "say", "about", "the", "case", "where", "the", "conduct", "be", "constitute", "the", "contempt", "as", "criminal", "under", "state", "law", "or", "even", "a", "felony", "but", "the", "state", "statute", "the", "state", "have", "a", "statute", "limit", "the", "penalty", "in", "contempt", "to", "say", "day", "in", "jail", "and", "fine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That would be -- that raises the question Mr. Justice White of the -- where the penalty is a trivial one.", "start": 1031.471, "stop": 1038.068, "duration": 6.6, "cleanText": [["that", "would", "be", "that", "raise", "the", "question", "mr", "justice", "white", "of", "the", "where", "the", "penalty", "be", "a", "trivial", "one"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "And that's -- and that is the limit of the judge's power in contempt?", "start": 1038.068, "stop": 1042.334, "duration": 4.27, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "and", "that", "be", "the", "limit", "of", "the", "judge", "s", "power", "in", "contempt"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, they could still proceed -- if this is what you're asking me.", "start": 1042.334, "stop": 1046.16, "duration": 3.83, "cleanText": [["well", "they", "could", "still", "proceed", "if", "this", "be", "what", "you", "be", "ask", "me"]]}, {"text": "They could still proceed by a way of criminal indictment.", "start": 1046.16, "stop": 1049.416, "duration": 3.26, "cleanText": [["they", "could", "still", "proceed", "by", "a", "way", "of", "criminal", "indictment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, but you -- yes.", "start": 1049.416, "stop": 1050.602, "duration": 1.19, "cleanText": [["yes", "but", "you", "yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Since there are no double jeopardy protections on this as you know it.", "start": 1050.602, "stop": 1053.868, "duration": 3.27, "cleanText": [["since", "there", "be", "no", "double", "jeopardy", "protection", "on", "this", "as", "you", "know", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1053.868, "stop": 1054.986, "duration": 1.12, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, which is one of the dangers by the way --", "start": 1054.986, "stop": 1056.558, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["oh", "which", "be", "one", "of", "the", "danger", "by", "the", "way"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "But you would still require a jury trial in the contempt action even though the penalty was a minor one?", "start": 1056.558, "stop": 1062.458, "duration": 5.9, "cleanText": [["but", "you", "would", "still", "require", "a", "jury", "trial", "in", "the", "contempt", "action", "even", "though", "the", "penalty", "be", "a", "minor", "one"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes sir.", "start": 1062.458, "stop": 1063.032, "duration": 0.57, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}, {"text": "I believe that's what --", "start": 1063.032, "stop": 1064.446, "duration": 1.41, "cleanText": [["i", "believe", "that", "be", "what"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why?", "start": 1064.446, "stop": 1065.981, "duration": 1.54, "cleanText": [["why"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, because I believe along with Mr. Justice Black and Mr. Justice Douglas that unless the legislature at some point makes the difference between -- the state's difference between what is petty and what is not petty that all criminal contempt must be considered the same.", "start": 1065.981, "stop": 1084.628, "duration": 18.65, "cleanText": [["well", "because", "i", "believe", "along", "with", "mr", "justice", "black", "and", "mr", "justice", "douglas", "that", "unless", "the", "legislature", "at", "some", "point", "make", "the", "difference", "between", "the", "state", "s", "difference", "between", "what", "be", "petty", "and", "what", "be", "not", "petty", "that", "all", "criminal", "contempt", "must", "be", "consider", "the", "same"]]}, {"text": "We do have that federally though we do not have it in the State of Illinois.", "start": 1084.628, "stop": 1088.909, "duration": 4.28, "cleanText": [["we", "do", "have", "that", "federally", "though", "we", "do", "not", "have", "it", "in", "the", "state", "of", "illinois"]]}, {"text": "I must point out that in the State of Illinois there is no definition of what constitutes a petty crime.", "start": 1088.909, "stop": 1096.772, "duration": 7.86, "cleanText": [["i", "must", "point", "out", "that", "in", "the", "state", "of", "illinois", "there", "be", "no", "definition", "of", "what", "constitute", "a", "petty", "crime"]]}, {"text": "Under the criminal code there, the petty -- crimes are -- consists of misdemeanors and felonies and that is all which is why I would ask in this case, should the Court see fit to go along with our brief that the case be remanded for a new trial rather than for the imposition of any six months sentence as was done in Cheff.", "start": 1096.772, "stop": 1124.579, "duration": 27.81, "cleanText": [["under", "the", "criminal", "code", "there", "the", "petty", "crime", "be", "consist", "of", "misdemeanor", "and", "felony", "and", "that", "be", "all", "which", "be", "why", "i", "would", "ask", "in", "this", "case", "should", "the", "court", "see", "fit", "to", "go", "along", "with", "our", "brief", "that", "the", "case", "be", "remand", "for", "a", "new", "trial", "rather", "than", "for", "the", "imposition", "of", "any", "six", "month", "sentence", "as", "be", "do", "in", "cheff"]]}, {"text": "Foreclosed, you know I see the hour is getting close.", "start": 1124.579, "stop": 1126.788, "duration": 2.21, "cleanText": [["foreclose", "you", "know", "i", "see", "the", "hour", "be", "get", "close"]]}, {"text": "I do want to call the Court's attention to the secret report which had been made by the amicus curiae to the judge.", "start": 1126.788, "stop": 1136.708, "duration": 9.92, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "want", "to", "call", "the", "court", "s", "attention", "to", "the", "secret", "report", "which", "have", "be", "make", "by", "the", "amicus", "curia", "to", "the", "judge"]]}, {"text": "We believe that under the decisions of this Court particularly In re Murchison which dealt with the one man grand jury in Michigan and In re Oliver also dealing with the same situation that it a -- is just constitutionally wrong for a judge at any time to have access to reports whether from his own agent as in this case in amicus curiae or anyone else in his possession prior to the trial and we believe that this is what the record establishes here.", "start": 1136.708, "stop": 1177.565, "duration": 40.86, "cleanText": [["we", "believe", "that", "under", "the", "decision", "of", "this", "court", "particularly", "in", "re", "murchison", "which", "deal", "with", "the", "one", "man", "grand", "jury", "in", "michigan", "and", "in", "re", "oliver", "also", "deal", "with", "the", "same", "situation", "that", "it", "a", "be", "just", "constitutionally", "wrong", "for", "a", "judge", "at", "any", "time", "to", "have", "access", "to", "report", "whether", "from", "his", "own", "agent", "as", "in", "this", "case", "in", "amicus", "curia", "or", "anyone", "else", "in", "his", "possession", "prior", "to", "the", "trial", "and", "we", "believe", "that", "this", "be", "what", "the", "record", "establish", "here"]]}, {"text": "I'd like with the permission of the Court to stop at this point.", "start": 1177.565, "stop": 1181.03, "duration": 3.46, "cleanText": [["I", "have", "like", "with", "the", "permission", "of", "the", "court", "to", "stop", "at", "this", "point"]]}, {"text": "I would like to reserve a few moments tomorrow for my rebuttal.", "start": 1181.03, "stop": 1187.759, "duration": 6.73, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "to", "reserve", "a", "few", "moment", "tomorrow", "for", "my", "rebuttal"]]}, {"text": "Thank you Your Honor.", "start": 1187.759, "stop": 1188.625, "duration": 0.87, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Go right ahead.", "start": 1188.625, "stop": 1190.409, "duration": 1.78, "cleanText": [["go", "right", "ahead"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "As I have asked to save a few minutes for my rebuttal.", "start": 1190.409, "stop": 1191.554, "duration": 1.14, "cleanText": [["as", "i", "have", "ask", "to", "save", "a", "few", "minute", "for", "my", "rebuttal"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, I'm really sorry.", "start": 1191.554, "stop": 1192.986, "duration": 1.43, "cleanText": [["oh", "I", "be", "really", "sorry"]]}, {"text": "Well, then we wont -- we'll recess now.", "start": 1192.986, "stop": 1196.22, "duration": 3.23, "cleanText": [["well", "then", "we", "will", "not", "we", "will", "recess", "now"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thanks.", "start": 1196.22, "stop": 1196.509, "duration": 0.29, "cleanText": [["thanks"]]}, {"text": "Thank you Your Honor.", "start": 1196.509, "stop": 1202.981, "duration": 6.47, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "your", "honor"]]}]}]}, {"transcriptTitle": "Oral Argument - January 17, 1968", "transcriptLink": "https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren15/oral_argument_audio/15539", "transcript": [{"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Number 52, S. Edward Bloom versus Illinois.", "start": 0, "stop": 7.536, "duration": 7.54, "cleanText": [["number", "s", "edward", "bloom", "versus", "illinois"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Eben have you concluded your argument, you have?", "start": 7.536, "stop": 10.291, "duration": 2.76, "cleanText": [["mr", "eben", "have", "you", "conclude", "your", "argument", "you", "have"]]}, {"text": "Had you not?", "start": 10.291, "stop": 11.332, "duration": 1.04, "cleanText": [["have", "you", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "May I please the Court.", "start": 11.332, "stop": 12.053, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["may", "i", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "I had terminated my opening as of yesterday.", "start": 12.053, "stop": 13.813, "duration": 1.76, "cleanText": [["i", "have", "terminate", "my", "opening", "as", "of", "yesterday"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes I understood that.", "start": 13.813, "stop": 14.889, "duration": 1.08, "cleanText": [["yes", "i", "understood", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you Your Honor.", "start": 14.889, "stop": 15.993, "duration": 1.1, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Hladis.", "start": 15.993, "stop": 24.803, "duration": 8.81, "cleanText": [["mr", "hladis"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court.", "start": 24.803, "stop": 29.255, "duration": 4.45, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "During the course yesterday afternoon's argument by counsel for the petitioner, he made two observations with which we must take issue.", "start": 29.255, "stop": 40.783, "duration": 11.53, "cleanText": [["during", "the", "course", "yesterday", "afternoon", "s", "argument", "by", "counsel", "for", "the", "petitioner", "he", "make", "two", "observation", "with", "which", "we", "must", "take", "issue"]]}, {"text": "One relates to the factual aspect of this case and the second relates to the law on the issue as it has been announced by this Court.", "start": 40.783, "stop": 53.355, "duration": 12.57, "cleanText": [["one", "relate", "to", "the", "factual", "aspect", "of", "this", "case", "and", "the", "second", "relates", "to", "the", "law", "on", "the", "issue", "as", "it", "have", "be", "announce", "by", "this", "court"]]}, {"text": "We address ourselves first to the factual aspect.", "start": 53.355, "stop": 57.355, "duration": 4, "cleanText": [["we", "address", "ourselves", "first", "to", "the", "factual", "aspect"]]}, {"text": "The key or the simple facts in this case are not many.", "start": 57.355, "stop": 62.219, "duration": 4.86, "cleanText": [["the", "key", "or", "the", "simple", "fact", "in", "this", "case", "be", "not", "many"]]}, {"text": "The decedent died on the 6th of July 1964.", "start": 62.219, "stop": 66.876, "duration": 4.66, "cleanText": [["the", "decedent", "die", "on", "the", "th", "of", "july"]]}, {"text": "On the 14th of July 1964, this petitioner drafted and caused the execution of a will of this dead person dated June 21, 1964 and on the 11th of August 1964, he presented his will for admission to probate in a probate division in Cook County and in this petition stated that the decedent had died on the 6th of July.", "start": 66.876, "stop": 91.984, "duration": 25.11, "cleanText": [["on", "the", "th", "of", "july", "this", "petitioner", "draft", "and", "cause", "the", "execution", "of", "a", "will", "of", "this", "dead", "person", "date", "june", "and", "on", "the", "th", "of", "august", "he", "present", "his", "will", "for", "admission", "to", "probate", "in", "a", "probate", "division", "in", "cook", "county", "and", "in", "this", "petition", "state", "that", "the", "decedent", "have", "die", "on", "the", "th", "of", "july"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is he beneficiary?", "start": 91.984, "stop": 93.761, "duration": 1.78, "cleanText": [["be", "he", "beneficiary"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No sir, he was not.", "start": 93.761, "stop": 95.948, "duration": 2.19, "cleanText": [["no", "sir", "he", "be", "not"]]}, {"text": "The record will show and our statement of facts indicates that it had actually began with a practical nurse by the name of Pauline Owens would increase her legacy in this fraudulent will from $20,000 and a valid will to $40,000 in this will.", "start": 95.948, "stop": 113.202, "duration": 17.25, "cleanText": [["the", "record", "will", "show", "and", "our", "statement", "of", "fact", "indicate", "that", "it", "have", "actually", "begin", "with", "a", "practical", "nurse", "by", "the", "name", "of", "pauline", "owen", "would", "increase", "her", "legacy", "in", "this", "fraudulent", "will", "from", "and", "a", "valid", "will", "to", "in", "this", "will"]]}, {"text": "Now the important consideration for the purposes of this case is this, yesterday the counsel referred to the alleged filing of a spurious will and two other alleged contemptuous acts.", "start": 113.202, "stop": 130.205, "duration": 17, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "important", "consideration", "for", "the", "purpose", "of", "this", "case", "be", "this", "yesterday", "the", "counsel", "refer", "to", "the", "allege", "filing", "of", "a", "spurious", "will", "and", "two", "other", "allege", "contemptuous", "act"]]}, {"text": "We submit gentlemen that on the basis of the record at this time and on the basis of the record as it was made in the Courts of Review in the State of Illinois it is improper for a counsel to refer to alleged contemptuous conduct because this petitioner has not only failed to challenge the sufficiency of the finding of guilt but he affirmatively conceded in the Supreme Court of Illinois that the findings of guilt were amply supported by the evidence.", "start": 130.205, "stop": 164.597, "duration": 34.39, "cleanText": [["we", "submit", "gentleman", "that", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "the", "record", "at", "this", "time", "and", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "the", "record", "as", "it", "be", "make", "in", "the", "court", "of", "review", "in", "the", "state", "of", "illinois", "it", "be", "improper", "for", "a", "counsel", "to", "refer", "to", "allege", "contemptuous", "conduct", "because", "this", "petitioner", "have", "not", "only", "fail", "to", "challenge", "the", "sufficiency", "of", "the", "finding", "of", "guilt", "but", "he", "affirmatively", "concede", "in", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "illinois", "that", "the", "finding", "of", "guilt", "we", "be", "amply", "support", "by", "the", "evidence"]]}, {"text": "Now we understand that the briefs filed by all parties are a part of the certiorari filed in this Court.", "start": 164.597, "stop": 172.277, "duration": 7.68, "cleanText": [["now", "we", "understand", "that", "the", "brief", "file", "by", "all", "party", "be", "a", "part", "of", "the", "certiorari", "file", "in", "this", "court"]]}, {"text": "That concession is found at page 15 of the petitioner's brief and the concession is also noted in the opinion of the Supreme Court of Illinois.", "start": 172.277, "stop": 182.656, "duration": 10.38, "cleanText": [["that", "concession", "be", "find", "at", "page", "of", "the", "petitioner", "s", "brief", "and", "the", "concession", "be", "also", "note", "in", "the", "opinion", "of", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "illinois"]]}, {"text": "Now what we are getting at is this, the case is here before this Court on the issue as to whether or not he was entitled to a jury trial.", "start": 182.656, "stop": 193.496, "duration": 10.84, "cleanText": [["now", "what", "we", "be", "get", "at", "be", "this", "the", "case", "be", "here", "before", "this", "court", "on", "the", "issue", "as", "to", "whether", "or", "not", "he", "be", "entitle", "to", "a", "jury", "trial"]]}, {"text": "But the very issue, the very point which a jury could give him to wit the finding of guilt or non-guilt, the finding of guilt or innocence is not challenged and has never been challenged.", "start": 193.496, "stop": 210.487, "duration": 16.99, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "very", "issue", "the", "very", "point", "which", "a", "jury", "could", "give", "him", "to", "wit", "the", "finding", "of", "guilt", "or", "non", "guilt", "the", "finding", "of", "guilt", "or", "innocence", "be", "not", "challenge", "and", "have", "never", "be", "challenge"]]}, {"text": "The second observation --", "start": 210.487, "stop": 210.829, "duration": 0.34, "cleanText": [["the", "second", "observation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "There was a challenge at the trial, wasn't it?", "start": 210.829, "stop": 212.962, "duration": 2.13, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "a", "challenge", "at", "the", "trial", "be", "not", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Beg pardon sir?", "start": 212.962, "stop": 213.513, "duration": 0.55, "cleanText": [["beg", "pardon", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "There was a challenge at the trial, wasn't it?", "start": 213.513, "stop": 215.865, "duration": 2.35, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "a", "challenge", "at", "the", "trial", "be", "not", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "In the sense that he cross-examined the prosecution witnesses.", "start": 215.865, "stop": 221.45, "duration": 5.58, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "sense", "that", "he", "cross", "examine", "the", "prosecution", "witness"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Pleaded not --", "start": 221.45, "stop": 222.658, "duration": 1.21, "cleanText": [["plead", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "He pleaded not guilty, yes.", "start": 222.658, "stop": 224.251, "duration": 1.59, "cleanText": [["he", "plead", "not", "guilty", "yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, isn't that a challenge?", "start": 224.251, "stop": 225.342, "duration": 1.09, "cleanText": [["well", "be", "not", "that", "a", "challenge"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is a challenge, yes.", "start": 225.342, "stop": 226.672, "duration": 1.33, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "a", "challenge", "yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well then he did at some time challenge it.", "start": 226.672, "stop": 228.476, "duration": 1.8, "cleanText": [["well", "then", "he", "do", "at", "some", "time", "challenge", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "He did it at the trial but the point is that after the finding of guilty was in, he did not challenge, not only did not challenge but he did concede that the findings were supported by the evidence.", "start": 228.476, "stop": 240.831, "duration": 12.35, "cleanText": [["he", "do", "it", "at", "the", "trial", "but", "the", "point", "be", "that", "after", "the", "finding", "of", "guilty", "be", "in", "he", "do", "not", "challenge", "not", "only", "do", "not", "challenge", "but", "he", "do", "concede", "that", "the", "finding", "we", "be", "support", "by", "the", "evidence"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, but aren't there issues here of alleged trial errors in respect to the psychiatric testimonies --", "start": 240.831, "stop": 251.244, "duration": 10.41, "cleanText": [["yes", "but", "be", "not", "there", "issue", "here", "of", "allege", "trial", "error", "in", "respect", "to", "the", "psychiatric", "testimony"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "He makes no --", "start": 251.244, "stop": 251.577, "duration": 0.33, "cleanText": [["he", "make", "no"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- and he (Voice Overlap) and there's something, I've forgotten --", "start": 251.577, "stop": 254.092, "duration": 2.52, "cleanText": [["and", "he", "voice", "overlap", "and", "there", "be", "something", "I", "have", "forget"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "You're talking about the amicus curiae report.", "start": 254.092, "stop": 256.805, "duration": 2.71, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "talk", "about", "the", "amicus", "curiae", "report"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, yes is that -- no, I'm not -- in addition to that am I wrong?", "start": 256.805, "stop": 260.516, "duration": 3.71, "cleanText": [["yes", "yes", "be", "that", "no", "I", "be", "not", "in", "addition", "to", "that", "be", "i", "wrong"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "And then the third observation he makes as the remark of the assistant state's attorney who have made reference to the fact that the petitioner did not take the stand.", "start": 260.516, "stop": 270.999, "duration": 10.48, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "the", "third", "observation", "he", "make", "as", "the", "remark", "of", "the", "assistant", "state", "s", "attorney", "who", "have", "make", "reference", "to", "the", "fact", "that", "the", "petitioner", "do", "not", "take", "the", "stand"]]}, {"text": "Now as to the first, the amicus curiae report that is a practice that has been approved by the Supreme Court of Illinois.", "start": 270.999, "stop": 278.894, "duration": 7.89, "cleanText": [["now", "as", "to", "the", "first", "the", "amicus", "curiae", "report", "that", "be", "a", "practice", "that", "have", "be", "approve", "by", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "illinois"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "No I think the reference maybe to your adversary's statement yesterday that testimony of the psychiatrist was abused to show that the petitioner could not possibly have committed this crime assuming to that effect.", "start": 278.894, "stop": 297.871, "duration": 18.98, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "think", "the", "reference", "maybe", "to", "your", "adversary", "s", "statement", "yesterday", "that", "testimony", "of", "the", "psychiatrist", "be", "abuse", "to", "show", "that", "the", "petitioner", "could", "not", "possibly", "have", "commit", "this", "crime", "assume", "to", "that", "effect"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 297.871, "stop": 299.894, "duration": 2.02, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "So that -- that would indicate that there was some sort of a contest at the trial level.", "start": 299.894, "stop": 305.732, "duration": 5.84, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "that", "would", "indicate", "that", "there", "be", "some", "sort", "of", "a", "contest", "at", "the", "trial", "level"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, we're not quarrelling the fact that there was a contest at the trial level.", "start": 305.732, "stop": 308.939, "duration": 3.21, "cleanText": [["oh", "we", "be", "not", "quarrel", "the", "fact", "that", "there", "be", "a", "contest", "at", "the", "trial", "level"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well what is your point then, (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 308.939, "stop": 310.172, "duration": 1.23, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "be", "your", "point", "then", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "The point is this that once the finding --", "start": 310.172, "stop": 311.987, "duration": 1.81, "cleanText": [["the", "point", "be", "this", "that", "once", "the", "finding"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "Not prejudicial error, what is it?", "start": 311.987, "stop": 314.159, "duration": 2.17, "cleanText": [["not", "prejudicial", "error", "what", "be", "it"]]}, {"text": "What is your point?", "start": 314.159, "stop": 315.354, "duration": 1.19, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "your", "point"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "The point is that what he wants today, it would seem to me that if I were in the petitioner's position and I were asking this Court to formulate a constitutional doctrine whereby I'd be guaranteed a jury trial in a criminal contempt case pursuant to the Sixth Amendment as it would be imposed upon our course by the Fourteenth Amendment that I would at least come up here where the bona fide contest on the findings of guilt.", "start": 315.354, "stop": 345.698, "duration": 30.34, "cleanText": [["the", "point", "be", "that", "what", "he", "want", "today", "it", "would", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "if", "i", "we", "be", "in", "the", "petitioner", "s", "position", "and", "i", "we", "be", "ask", "this", "court", "to", "formulate", "a", "constitutional", "doctrine", "whereby", "I", "would", "be", "guarantee", "a", "jury", "trial", "in", "a", "criminal", "contempt", "case", "pursuant", "to", "the", "sixth", "amendment", "as", "it", "would", "be", "impose", "upon", "our", "course", "by", "the", "fourteenth", "amendment", "that", "i", "would", "at", "least", "come", "up", "here", "where", "the", "bona", "fide", "contest", "on", "the", "finding", "of", "guilt"]]}, {"text": "But he didn't even do that --", "start": 345.698, "stop": 347.31, "duration": 1.61, "cleanText": [["but", "he", "do", "not", "even", "do", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 347.31, "stop": 347.402, "duration": 0.09, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- in the Courts of Review in the State of Illinois sir.", "start": 347.402, "stop": 349.427, "duration": 2.03, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "court", "of", "review", "in", "the", "state", "of", "illinois", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "I confess that I still don't follow you.", "start": 349.427, "stop": 351.927, "duration": 2.5, "cleanText": [["i", "confess", "that", "i", "still", "do", "not", "follow", "you"]]}, {"text": "Are you saying that there was a contest on the issue of guilt but not a substantial one, is that your point?", "start": 351.927, "stop": 358.176, "duration": 6.25, "cleanText": [["be", "you", "say", "that", "there", "be", "a", "contest", "on", "the", "issue", "of", "guilt", "but", "not", "a", "substantial", "one", "be", "that", "your", "point"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "What I am saying is that after the finding was made, he not only did not challenge the sufficiency but he actually conceded that the evidence was sufficient to support the findings.", "start": 358.176, "stop": 368.299, "duration": 10.12, "cleanText": [["what", "i", "be", "say", "be", "that", "after", "the", "finding", "be", "make", "he", "not", "only", "do", "not", "challenge", "the", "sufficiency", "but", "he", "actually", "concede", "that", "the", "evidence", "be", "sufficient", "to", "support", "the", "finding"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I know but I thought you said yesterday and as I read his brief, it's an issue he thought of malevolent intent, is that the language which he says is important and that psychiatric test to only bears on it and that he could not have been guilty of the offense because the psychiatric testimony might have persuaded the jury, indicated that he did not have the necessary malevolent intent which -- as I understood your argument.", "start": 368.299, "stop": 398.48, "duration": 30.18, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "know", "but", "i", "think", "you", "say", "yesterday", "and", "as", "i", "read", "his", "brief", "it", "be", "an", "issue", "he", "think", "of", "malevolent", "intent", "be", "that", "the", "language", "which", "he", "say", "be", "important", "and", "that", "psychiatric", "test", "to", "only", "bear", "on", "it", "and", "that", "he", "could", "not", "have", "be", "guilty", "of", "the", "offense", "because", "the", "psychiatric", "testimony", "might", "have", "persuade", "the", "jury", "indicate", "that", "he", "do", "not", "have", "the", "necessary", "malevolent", "intent", "which", "as", "i", "understand", "your", "argument"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 398.48, "stop": 399.196, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "That was advanced sir.", "start": 399.196, "stop": 401.292, "duration": 2.1, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "advanced", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "But even if he raise no question -- any square attack on the findings, your argument would apply to any other trial error.", "start": 401.292, "stop": 413.2, "duration": 11.91, "cleanText": [["but", "even", "if", "he", "raise", "no", "question", "any", "square", "attack", "on", "the", "finding", "your", "argument", "would", "apply", "to", "any", "other", "trial", "error"]]}, {"text": "And you want to raise a trial error you better accompany it with a challenge to the facts.", "start": 413.2, "stop": 419.456, "duration": 6.26, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "want", "to", "raise", "a", "trial", "error", "you", "good", "accompany", "it", "with", "a", "challenge", "to", "the", "fact"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would think so.", "start": 419.456, "stop": 421.097, "duration": 1.64, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "think", "so"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that --", "start": 421.097, "stop": 421.374, "duration": 0.28, "cleanText": [["well", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because I think --", "start": 421.374, "stop": 423.007, "duration": 1.63, "cleanText": [["because", "i", "think"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "That just doesn't --", "start": 423.007, "stop": 425.046, "duration": 2.04, "cleanText": [["that", "just", "do", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Gentlemen, I think he'd -- if he has a case, I don't think it's a Sixth Amendment case.", "start": 425.046, "stop": 430.562, "duration": 5.52, "cleanText": [["gentleman", "i", "think", "he", "would", "if", "he", "have", "a", "case", "i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "be", "a", "sixth", "amendment", "case"]]}, {"text": "I think what he's actually complaining about is the extent of the punishment and that would be our solution to the problem, it's a Fourteenth Amendment problem.", "start": 430.562, "stop": 441.068, "duration": 10.51, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "what", "he", "be", "actually", "complain", "about", "be", "the", "extent", "of", "the", "punishment", "and", "that", "would", "be", "our", "solution", "to", "the", "problem", "it", "be", "a", "fourteenth", "amendment", "problem"]]}, {"text": "The issue on the case as we have it here is not whether he should have been given a jury trial.", "start": 441.068, "stop": 448.913, "duration": 7.85, "cleanText": [["the", "issue", "on", "the", "case", "as", "we", "have", "it", "here", "be", "not", "whether", "he", "should", "have", "be", "give", "a", "jury", "trial"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well let's just assume that if -- let's just assume that in the federal system for example, a man demands a jury trial in a criminal case and is denied.", "start": 448.913, "stop": 459.162, "duration": 10.25, "cleanText": [["well", "let", "us", "just", "assume", "that", "if", "let", "us", "just", "assume", "that", "in", "the", "federal", "system", "for", "example", "a", "man", "demand", "a", "jury", "trial", "in", "a", "criminal", "case", "and", "be", "deny"]]}, {"text": "And the judge finds him guilty and he comes up solely on the refusal of the jury trial.", "start": 459.162, "stop": 468.822, "duration": 9.66, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "judge", "find", "him", "guilty", "and", "he", "come", "up", "solely", "on", "the", "refusal", "of", "the", "jury", "trial"]]}, {"text": "Would you say to him that -- would you say to him, No, your challenge can't be sustained because you don't challenge the finding of guilt?", "start": 468.822, "stop": 477.79, "duration": 8.97, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "say", "to", "him", "that", "would", "you", "say", "to", "him", "no", "your", "challenge", "can", "not", "be", "sustain", "because", "you", "do", "not", "challenge", "the", "finding", "of", "guilt"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I would not Mr. Justice White for a different reason though, because it's clearly established under the Sixth Amendment and under Article III that any criminal case, he is entitled to a jury trial.", "start": 477.79, "stop": 489.178, "duration": 11.39, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "would", "not", "mr", "justice", "white", "for", "a", "different", "reason", "though", "because", "it", "be", "clearly", "establish", "under", "the", "sixth", "amendment", "and", "under", "article", "iii", "that", "any", "criminal", "case", "he", "be", "entitle", "to", "a", "jury", "trial"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's exactly what he's claim is here that under the Sixth Amendment --", "start": 489.178, "stop": 492.09, "duration": 2.91, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "exactly", "what", "he", "be", "claim", "be", "here", "that", "under", "the", "sixth", "amendment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 492.09, "stop": 492.518, "duration": 0.43, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "Well, what he's doing here is asking this Court --", "start": 492.518, "stop": 495.745, "duration": 3.23, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "he", "be", "do", "here", "be", "ask", "this", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Surely --", "start": 495.745, "stop": 496.382, "duration": 0.64, "cleanText": [["surely"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- to formulate a new doctrine --", "start": 496.382, "stop": 498.329, "duration": 1.95, "cleanText": [["to", "formulate", "a", "new", "doctrine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right.", "start": 498.329, "stop": 499, "duration": 0.67, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- one which has never been formulated before which even in Cheff has contrary to his representation has no constitutional basis at all and is asking this Court to say now under the Sixth Amendment criminal contempt cases shall have jury trials and will impose it on the state by virtue --", "start": 499, "stop": 517.311, "duration": 18.31, "cleanText": [["one", "which", "have", "never", "be", "formulate", "before", "which", "even", "in", "cheff", "have", "contrary", "to", "his", "representation", "have", "no", "constitutional", "basis", "at", "all", "and", "be", "ask", "this", "court", "to", "say", "now", "under", "the", "sixth", "amendment", "criminal", "contempt", "case", "shall", "have", "jury", "trial", "and", "will", "impose", "it", "on", "the", "state", "by", "virtue"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "What you're really saying is a kind of an (Inaudible) argument.", "start": 517.311, "stop": 522.506, "duration": 5.19, "cleanText": [["what", "you", "be", "really", "say", "be", "a", "kind", "of", "an", "inaudible", "argument"]]}, {"text": "The case is (Inaudible) as unappealing to this from your standing problem.", "start": 522.506, "stop": 527.448, "duration": 4.94, "cleanText": [["the", "case", "be", "inaudible", "as", "unappealing", "to", "this", "from", "your", "stand", "problem"]]}, {"text": "This Court should not ceasefire to (Inaudible) basic constitution doctrine, isn't that what you're saying?", "start": 527.448, "stop": 536.268, "duration": 8.82, "cleanText": [["this", "court", "should", "not", "ceasefire", "to", "inaudible", "basic", "constitution", "doctrine", "be", "not", "that", "what", "you", "be", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that is not the only reason that we would say it Your Honor because we --", "start": 536.268, "stop": 539.298, "duration": 3.03, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "be", "not", "the", "only", "reason", "that", "we", "would", "say", "it", "your", "honor", "because", "we"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "This facet of your argument comes after that.", "start": 539.298, "stop": 542.925, "duration": 3.63, "cleanText": [["this", "facet", "of", "your", "argument", "come", "after", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct, that is correct.", "start": 542.925, "stop": 546.224, "duration": 3.3, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "What do you have to say about the fact that this is also a felony under the laws of Illinois, forgery?", "start": 546.224, "stop": 555.934, "duration": 9.71, "cleanText": [["what", "do", "you", "have", "to", "say", "about", "the", "fact", "that", "this", "be", "also", "a", "felony", "under", "the", "law", "of", "illinois", "forgery"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes it is.", "start": 555.934, "stop": 559.882, "duration": 3.95, "cleanText": [["yes", "it", "be"]]}, {"text": "I don't see any inconsistency between the two at all.", "start": 559.882, "stop": 563.624, "duration": 3.74, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "see", "any", "inconsistency", "between", "the", "two", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "We have here --", "start": 563.624, "stop": 564.254, "duration": 0.63, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Wouldn't it be inconsistent if you had a choice of trying the man for the same act, one with the jury and one without?", "start": 564.254, "stop": 574.766, "duration": 10.51, "cleanText": [["would", "not", "it", "be", "inconsistent", "if", "you", "have", "a", "choice", "of", "try", "the", "man", "for", "the", "same", "act", "one", "with", "the", "jury", "and", "one", "without"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, by the very nature of the two proceedings.", "start": 574.766, "stop": 578.374, "duration": 3.61, "cleanText": [["no", "by", "the", "very", "nature", "of", "the", "two", "proceeding"]]}, {"text": "And the one you have contempt which is --", "start": 578.374, "stop": 580.661, "duration": 2.29, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "one", "you", "have", "contempt", "which", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "But do you take the position they could also be charged with forgery?", "start": 580.661, "stop": 584.644, "duration": 3.98, "cleanText": [["but", "do", "you", "take", "the", "position", "they", "could", "also", "be", "charge", "with", "forgery"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "It is possible, but I say that as far as Cook County is concerned that will not happen and as a matter of fact, the statute has run in this particular case.", "start": 584.644, "stop": 592.437, "duration": 7.79, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "possible", "but", "i", "say", "that", "as", "far", "as", "cook", "county", "be", "concern", "that", "will", "not", "happen", "and", "as", "a", "matter", "of", "fact", "the", "statute", "have", "run", "in", "this", "particular", "case"]]}, {"text": "But we have had rare instances where contempts have been committed usually in a probate level which are also felonies.", "start": 592.437, "stop": 600.385, "duration": 7.95, "cleanText": [["but", "we", "have", "have", "rare", "instance", "where", "contempt", "have", "be", "commit", "usually", "in", "a", "probate", "level", "which", "be", "also", "felony"]]}, {"text": "And in all cases where the probate judge has gone to the way of contempt, the state has not prosecuted criminally and we did not do it here and we don't -- certainly don't intend to do it.", "start": 600.385, "stop": 610.113, "duration": 9.73, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "all", "case", "where", "the", "probate", "judge", "have", "go", "to", "the", "way", "of", "contempt", "the", "state", "have", "not", "prosecute", "criminally", "and", "we", "do", "not", "do", "it", "here", "and", "we", "do", "not", "certainly", "do", "not", "intend", "to", "do", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Who's -- makes the choice?", "start": 610.113, "stop": 612.995, "duration": 2.88, "cleanText": [["who", "be", "make", "the", "choice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "In this case the errors themselves made the choice.", "start": 612.995, "stop": 615.593, "duration": 2.6, "cleanText": [["in", "this", "case", "the", "error", "themselves", "make", "the", "choice"]]}, {"text": "They are the ones that began.", "start": 615.593, "stop": 617.228, "duration": 1.63, "cleanText": [["they", "be", "the", "one", "that", "begin"]]}, {"text": "They asked for the appointment of the amicus curiae and they filed a first petition or rule to show a cause and then the judge determined that there was probable cause after he had received the amicus curiae report and the contempt proceeding began.", "start": 617.228, "stop": 631.464, "duration": 14.24, "cleanText": [["they", "ask", "for", "the", "appointment", "of", "the", "amicus", "curia", "and", "they", "file", "a", "first", "petition", "or", "rule", "to", "show", "a", "because", "and", "then", "the", "judge", "determine", "that", "there", "be", "probable", "because", "after", "he", "have", "receive", "the", "amicus", "curiae", "report", "and", "the", "contempt", "proceeding", "begin"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well isn't the contempt proceeding easier than going to a grand jury and trying the case before a jury?", "start": 631.464, "stop": 638.568, "duration": 7.1, "cleanText": [["well", "be", "not", "the", "contempt", "proceed", "easy", "than", "go", "to", "a", "grand", "jury", "and", "try", "the", "case", "before", "a", "jury"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would think it's easier and I would think it is much more effective and that is undoubtedly what the probate judge wanted to achieve in this particular case.", "start": 638.568, "stop": 648.149, "duration": 9.58, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "think", "it", "be", "easy", "and", "i", "would", "think", "it", "be", "much", "more", "effective", "and", "that", "be", "undoubtedly", "what", "the", "probate", "judge", "want", "to", "achieve", "in", "this", "particular", "case"]]}, {"text": "Because you're talking about a court in a large metropolitan area and as we all know much of the practice in a probate division is done what I might call on an ex parte basis because many times the interested party do not have counsel, they rely upon counsel for the personal representative.", "start": 648.149, "stop": 669.136, "duration": 20.99, "cleanText": [["because", "you", "be", "talk", "about", "a", "court", "in", "a", "large", "metropolitan", "area", "and", "as", "we", "all", "know", "much", "of", "the", "practice", "in", "a", "probate", "division", "be", "do", "what", "i", "might", "call", "on", "an", "ex", "parte", "basis", "because", "many", "time", "the", "interested", "party", "do", "not", "have", "counsel", "they", "rely", "upon", "counsel", "for", "the", "personal", "representative"]]}, {"text": "And the Court must rely upon the integrity, upon the honesty of the attorneys presenting matters to them.", "start": 669.136, "stop": 677.389, "duration": 8.25, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "court", "must", "rely", "upon", "the", "integrity", "upon", "the", "honesty", "of", "the", "attorney", "present", "matter", "to", "them"]]}, {"text": "And whereas in this case, you have a situation where a fraudulent will was presented for admission and sought to be processed while the Court has a real problem as far as discipline is concerned.", "start": 677.389, "stop": 689.765, "duration": 12.38, "cleanText": [["and", "whereas", "in", "this", "case", "you", "have", "a", "situation", "where", "a", "fraudulent", "will", "be", "present", "for", "admission", "and", "seek", "to", "be", "process", "while", "the", "court", "have", "a", "real", "problem", "as", "far", "as", "discipline", "be", "concern"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you have a double jeopardy provision in your state constitution?", "start": 689.765, "stop": 693.328, "duration": 3.56, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "have", "a", "double", "jeopardy", "provision", "in", "your", "state", "constitution"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes we do sir.", "start": 693.328, "stop": 694.594, "duration": 1.27, "cleanText": [["yes", "we", "do", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Supposing (Inaudible) statute of limitation describing the process, this fellow, could he plead and -- his contempt conviction in regard of that (Inaudible).", "start": 694.594, "stop": 706.492, "duration": 11.9, "cleanText": [["suppose", "inaudible", "statute", "of", "limitation", "describe", "the", "process", "this", "fellow", "could", "he", "plead", "and", "his", "contempt", "conviction", "in", "regard", "of", "that", "inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't think he could Your Honor.", "start": 706.492, "stop": 708.582, "duration": 2.09, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "he", "could", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why?", "start": 708.582, "stop": 711.607, "duration": 3.02, "cleanText": [["why"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think strictly speaking, the doctrine of double jeopardy doesn't apply.", "start": 711.607, "stop": 715.417, "duration": 3.81, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "strictly", "speak", "the", "doctrine", "of", "double", "jeopardy", "do", "not", "apply"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "I beg your pardon.", "start": 715.417, "stop": 716.018, "duration": 0.6, "cleanText": [["i", "beg", "your", "pardon"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think they're strictly speaking the doctrine of double jeopardy would not apply --", "start": 716.018, "stop": 719.711, "duration": 3.69, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "they", "be", "strictly", "speak", "the", "doctrine", "of", "double", "jeopardy", "would", "not", "apply"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why?", "start": 719.711, "stop": 720.035, "duration": 0.32, "cleanText": [["why"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- to a criminal contempt.", "start": 720.035, "stop": 722.535, "duration": 2.5, "cleanText": [["to", "a", "criminal", "contempt"]]}, {"text": "I just don't think it would apply, its not a crime.", "start": 722.535, "stop": 726.862, "duration": 4.33, "cleanText": [["i", "just", "do", "not", "think", "it", "would", "apply", "its", "not", "a", "crime"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Suppose there is an uproar in the Court then, someone was murdered and the judge determined instead of having him indicted -- a person indicted for murder, he charge him with criminal contempt, could he try him for the murder and contempt?", "start": 726.862, "stop": 746.454, "duration": 19.59, "cleanText": [["suppose", "there", "be", "an", "uproar", "in", "the", "court", "then", "someone", "be", "murder", "and", "the", "judge", "determine", "instead", "of", "have", "him", "indict", "a", "person", "indict", "for", "murder", "he", "charge", "him", "with", "criminal", "contempt", "could", "he", "try", "him", "for", "the", "murder", "and", "contempt"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I imagine possibly he might -- well, that's not a probability actually Your Honor, I --", "start": 746.454, "stop": 751.811, "duration": 5.36, "cleanText": [["i", "imagine", "possibly", "he", "might", "well", "that", "be", "not", "a", "probability", "actually", "your", "honor", "i"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, why is it?", "start": 751.811, "stop": 752.699, "duration": 0.89, "cleanText": [["well", "why", "be", "it"]]}, {"text": "This -- what's the difference between forgery and murder if they're both statutory crimes and they are felonies?", "start": 752.699, "stop": 759.285, "duration": 6.59, "cleanText": [["this", "what", "be", "the", "difference", "between", "forgery", "and", "murder", "if", "they", "be", "both", "statutory", "crime", "and", "they", "be", "felony"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because of the gravity between the two.", "start": 759.285, "stop": 761.179, "duration": 1.89, "cleanText": [["because", "of", "the", "gravity", "between", "the", "two"]]}, {"text": "I mean one is -- that the forgery in this particular instance have to do with the very operation of the Court whereas certainly the murder would cause a disturbance in the Court but I just cannot visualize that the -- a probate Judge would move by way of contempt rather than have it in turn, the matter over the state for prosecution under the murder statute.", "start": 761.179, "stop": 784.82, "duration": 23.64, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "one", "be", "that", "the", "forgery", "in", "this", "particular", "instance", "have", "to", "do", "with", "the", "very", "operation", "of", "the", "court", "whereas", "certainly", "the", "murder", "would", "because", "a", "disturbance", "in", "the", "court", "but", "i", "just", "can", "not", "visualize", "that", "the", "a", "probate", "judge", "would", "move", "by", "way", "of", "contempt", "rather", "than", "have", "it", "in", "turn", "the", "matter", "over", "the", "state", "for", "prosecution", "under", "the", "murder", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that's why we're here today.", "start": 784.82, "stop": 786.125, "duration": 1.3, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "be", "why", "we", "be", "here", "today"]]}, {"text": "Some people think that forgery is a pretty important case and particularly when a man goes to jail for -- goes to penitentiary for years and they think they can't understand why it should be done in this way rather than give a man a jury after an indictment.", "start": 786.125, "stop": 805.061, "duration": 18.94, "cleanText": [["some", "people", "think", "that", "forgery", "be", "a", "pretty", "important", "case", "and", "particularly", "when", "a", "man", "go", "to", "jail", "for", "go", "to", "penitentiary", "for", "year", "and", "they", "think", "they", "can", "not", "understand", "why", "it", "should", "be", "do", "in", "this", "way", "rather", "than", "give", "a", "man", "a", "jury", "after", "an", "indictment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Mr. Chief Justice, I gave what we submit as a good practical sound reason in this particular context and that --", "start": 805.061, "stop": 813.381, "duration": 8.32, "cleanText": [["well", "mr", "chief", "justice", "i", "give", "what", "we", "submit", "as", "a", "good", "practical", "sound", "reason", "in", "this", "particular", "context", "and", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "But we're not dealing with practical reasons, particularly we're dealing with the law in this case.", "start": 813.381, "stop": 818.132, "duration": 4.75, "cleanText": [["but", "we", "be", "not", "deal", "with", "practical", "reason", "particularly", "we", "be", "deal", "with", "the", "law", "in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I understand but by the same token, that probate judge down there has to serve a notice upon the bar that he cannot tolerate practices such as we had here.", "start": 818.132, "stop": 829.845, "duration": 11.71, "cleanText": [["i", "understand", "but", "by", "the", "same", "token", "that", "probate", "judge", "down", "there", "have", "to", "serve", "a", "notice", "upon", "the", "bar", "that", "he", "can", "not", "tolerate", "practice", "such", "as", "we", "have", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well do you think it wouldn't be serving a notice on them if he called it detention of the grand jury and the grand jury indict him and he was convicted of forgery and sent to the penitentiary on what you say is absolutely conclusive evidence, wouldn't he trust a jury?", "start": 829.845, "stop": 846.425, "duration": 16.58, "cleanText": [["well", "do", "you", "think", "it", "would", "not", "be", "serve", "a", "notice", "on", "them", "if", "he", "call", "it", "detention", "of", "the", "grand", "jury", "and", "the", "grand", "jury", "indict", "him", "and", "he", "be", "convict", "of", "forgery", "and", "send", "to", "the", "penitentiary", "on", "what", "you", "say", "be", "absolutely", "conclusive", "evidence", "would", "not", "he", "trust", "a", "jury"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't think that as far as he was concerned it would be as effective.", "start": 846.425, "stop": 850.673, "duration": 4.25, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "that", "as", "far", "as", "he", "be", "concern", "it", "would", "be", "as", "effective"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why?", "start": 850.673, "stop": 852.072, "duration": 1.4, "cleanText": [["why"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I mean, if we -- would probably feel that he would deliver a better message to the bar then refer it all to the grand jury.", "start": 852.072, "stop": 859.166, "duration": 7.09, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "if", "we", "would", "probably", "feel", "that", "he", "would", "deliver", "a", "good", "message", "to", "the", "bar", "then", "refer", "it", "all", "to", "the", "grand", "jury"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "And then he uses his personal feelings in the matter to determine whether he wants to punish him on his own trial rather than to trust it to a jury.", "start": 859.166, "stop": 868.988, "duration": 9.82, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "he", "use", "his", "personal", "feeling", "in", "the", "matter", "to", "determine", "whether", "he", "want", "to", "punish", "him", "on", "his", "own", "trial", "rather", "than", "to", "trust", "it", "to", "a", "jury"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, whether we want to call it feelings or what or convictions but those are his views.", "start": 868.988, "stop": 874.373, "duration": 5.38, "cleanText": [["well", "whether", "we", "want", "to", "call", "it", "feel", "or", "what", "or", "conviction", "but", "those", "be", "his", "view"]]}, {"text": "And of course, here, as I pointed out before is the fact that the proceedings were actually initiated by the error, the lawful errors themselves.", "start": 874.373, "stop": 885.376, "duration": 11, "cleanText": [["and", "of", "course", "here", "as", "i", "point", "out", "before", "be", "the", "fact", "that", "the", "proceeding", "we", "be", "actually", "initiate", "by", "the", "error", "the", "lawful", "error", "themselves"]]}, {"text": "This is not something that was done completely on his own volition.", "start": 885.376, "stop": 898.407, "duration": 13.03, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "not", "something", "that", "be", "do", "completely", "on", "his", "own", "volition"]]}, {"text": "The --", "start": 898.407, "stop": 899.913, "duration": 1.51, "cleanText": [["the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Which do you think would be worse, to be disbarred or fined $2000?", "start": 899.913, "stop": 909.185, "duration": 9.27, "cleanText": [["which", "do", "you", "think", "would", "be", "bad", "to", "be", "disbar", "or", "fin"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Which would I --", "start": 909.185, "stop": 909.777, "duration": 0.59, "cleanText": [["which", "would", "i"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "On the life of the individuals.", "start": 909.777, "stop": 913.264, "duration": 3.49, "cleanText": [["on", "the", "life", "of", "the", "individual"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "The fine?", "start": 913.264, "stop": 913.972, "duration": 0.71, "cleanText": [["the", "fine"]]}, {"text": "Which would be worse?", "start": 913.972, "stop": 914.894, "duration": 0.92, "cleanText": [["which", "would", "be", "bad"]]}, {"text": "Disbarment.", "start": 914.894, "stop": 916.13, "duration": 1.24, "cleanText": [["disbarment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Disbarment, why?", "start": 916.13, "stop": 916.761, "duration": 0.63, "cleanText": [["disbarment", "why"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Disbarment.", "start": 916.761, "stop": 919.163, "duration": 2.4, "cleanText": [["disbarment"]]}, {"text": "Well, I think all of us as lawyers are pretty proud of our license and we do not want to be placed in a position of ever losing it.", "start": 919.163, "stop": 926.746, "duration": 7.58, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "all", "of", "us", "as", "lawyer", "be", "pretty", "proud", "of", "our", "license", "and", "we", "do", "not", "want", "to", "be", "place", "in", "a", "position", "of", "ever", "lose", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Not merely because of a foul of it, is it?", "start": 926.746, "stop": 928.965, "duration": 2.22, "cleanText": [["not", "merely", "because", "of", "a", "foul", "of", "it", "be", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I beg your pardon?", "start": 928.965, "stop": 930.012, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["i", "beg", "your", "pardon"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "It's not merely he's out of it, is he?", "start": 930.012, "stop": 934.52, "duration": 4.51, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "merely", "he", "be", "out", "of", "it", "be", "he"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think that is one of the elements, yes.", "start": 934.52, "stop": 937.062, "duration": 2.54, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "be", "one", "of", "the", "element", "yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "But isn't the main thing is his life's vocation is -- what (Inaudible) says, \"You've taken away that which is the most valuable thing perhaps to many lawyers have in the world\".", "start": 937.062, "stop": 947.392, "duration": 10.33, "cleanText": [["but", "be", "not", "the", "main", "thing", "be", "his", "life", "s", "vocation", "be", "what", "inaudible", "say", "you", "have", "take", "away", "that", "which", "be", "the", "most", "valuable", "thing", "perhaps", "to", "many", "lawyer", "have", "in", "the", "world"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I agree with you.", "start": 947.392, "stop": 949.025, "duration": 1.63, "cleanText": [["i", "agree", "with", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "And yet you say that he should not be considered as a criminal offense.", "start": 949.025, "stop": 956.225, "duration": 7.2, "cleanText": [["and", "yet", "you", "say", "that", "he", "should", "not", "be", "consider", "as", "a", "criminal", "offense"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well I don't, I don't know whether this contempt would conform the fair basis --", "start": 956.225, "stop": 959.941, "duration": 3.72, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "do", "not", "i", "do", "not", "know", "whether", "this", "contempt", "would", "conform", "the", "fair", "basis"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, why do they call it criminal?", "start": 959.941, "stop": 963.523, "duration": 3.58, "cleanText": [["well", "why", "do", "they", "call", "it", "criminal"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "As against civil?", "start": 963.523, "stop": 965.17, "duration": 1.65, "cleanText": [["as", "against", "civil"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why is it called criminal contempt?", "start": 965.17, "stop": 968.128, "duration": 2.96, "cleanText": [["why", "be", "it", "call", "criminal", "contempt"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think the reason that it's called criminal contempt is the fact that the Court as an agency of the public is actually in the -- is the agent of the public and that the public's dignity is offended by specific conduct.", "start": 968.128, "stop": 980.647, "duration": 12.52, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "the", "reason", "that", "it", "be", "call", "criminal", "contempt", "be", "the", "fact", "that", "the", "court", "as", "an", "agency", "of", "the", "public", "be", "actually", "in", "the", "be", "the", "agent", "of", "the", "public", "and", "that", "the", "public", "s", "dignity", "be", "offend", "by", "specific", "conduct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "And it's taking away from him if he is disbarred, is it not?", "start": 980.647, "stop": 984.519, "duration": 3.87, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "be", "take", "away", "from", "him", "if", "he", "be", "disbar", "be", "it", "not"]]}, {"text": "Far more that it would be if they took away his home or a large part of his property.", "start": 984.519, "stop": 990.346, "duration": 5.83, "cleanText": [["far", "more", "that", "it", "would", "be", "if", "they", "take", "away", "his", "home", "or", "a", "large", "part", "of", "his", "property"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, of course Mr. Justice Black we are assuming that --", "start": 990.346, "stop": 996.976, "duration": 6.63, "cleanText": [["well", "of", "course", "mr", "justice", "black", "we", "be", "assume", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, isn't it a not more valuable to him than his home would be?", "start": 996.976, "stop": 1001.639, "duration": 4.66, "cleanText": [["well", "be", "not", "it", "a", "not", "more", "valuable", "to", "him", "than", "his", "home", "would", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, yes, I would --", "start": 1001.639, "stop": 1002.215, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["oh", "yes", "i", "would"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Or a large part of his property.", "start": 1002.215, "stop": 1004.354, "duration": 2.14, "cleanText": [["or", "a", "large", "part", "of", "his", "property"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "As far as I -- personally I'm concerned, it would be, yes.", "start": 1004.354, "stop": 1008.373, "duration": 4.02, "cleanText": [["as", "far", "as", "i", "personally", "I", "be", "concerned", "it", "would", "be", "yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "In the Illinois --", "start": 1008.373, "stop": 1008.502, "duration": 0.13, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "illinois"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "But how can you not face the fact as it is, that it amount everywhere in the world that a human being can think of pragmatically that one of the worse punishments that can be inflicted on a human being.", "start": 1008.502, "stop": 1022.903, "duration": 14.4, "cleanText": [["but", "how", "can", "you", "not", "face", "the", "fact", "as", "it", "be", "that", "it", "amount", "everywhere", "in", "the", "world", "that", "a", "human", "be", "can", "think", "of", "pragmatically", "that", "one", "of", "the", "bad", "punishment", "that", "can", "be", "inflict", "on", "a", "human", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Are you speaking of disbarment now sir?", "start": 1022.903, "stop": 1024.236, "duration": 1.33, "cleanText": [["be", "you", "speak", "of", "disbarment", "now", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Disbarment.", "start": 1024.236, "stop": 1024.964, "duration": 0.73, "cleanText": [["disbarment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "The disbarment.", "start": 1024.964, "stop": 1026.561, "duration": 1.6, "cleanText": [["the", "disbarment"]]}, {"text": "I can't quarrel with that.", "start": 1026.561, "stop": 1028.963, "duration": 2.4, "cleanText": [["i", "can", "not", "quarrel", "with", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "What's the rule in Illinois, is conviction over felony automatic disbarment or not?", "start": 1028.963, "stop": 1033.359, "duration": 4.4, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "the", "rule", "in", "illinois", "be", "conviction", "over", "felony", "automatic", "disbarment", "or", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "It's not.", "start": 1033.359, "stop": 1034.576, "duration": 1.22, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "It's not?", "start": 1034.576, "stop": 1034.907, "duration": 0.33, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "It is not, no.", "start": 1034.907, "stop": 1035.905, "duration": 1, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "no"]]}, {"text": "The disbarment proceedings are conducted through grievance committees of the Bar Association --", "start": 1035.905, "stop": 1044.217, "duration": 8.31, "cleanText": [["the", "disbarment", "proceeding", "be", "conduct", "through", "grievance", "committee", "of", "the", "bar", "association"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I assume (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 1044.217, "stop": 1044.252, "duration": 0.03, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "assume", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- to the commissioners --", "start": 1044.252, "stop": 1045.472, "duration": 1.22, "cleanText": [["to", "the", "commissioner"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "I assume that but if he's convicted of a felony as the usual procedure that he is disbarred.", "start": 1045.472, "stop": 1050.61, "duration": 5.14, "cleanText": [["i", "assume", "that", "but", "if", "he", "be", "convict", "of", "a", "felony", "as", "the", "usual", "procedure", "that", "he", "be", "disbar"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, it's not automatic disbarment.", "start": 1050.61, "stop": 1052.619, "duration": 2.01, "cleanText": [["no", "it", "be", "not", "automatic", "disbarment"]]}, {"text": "He has his hearing --", "start": 1052.619, "stop": 1053.302, "duration": 0.68, "cleanText": [["he", "have", "his", "hearing"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Usual was my word.", "start": 1053.302, "stop": 1054.788, "duration": 1.49, "cleanText": [["usual", "be", "my", "word"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No it's not even that sir.", "start": 1054.788, "stop": 1056.571, "duration": 1.78, "cleanText": [["no", "it", "be", "not", "even", "that", "sir"]]}, {"text": "And he asks this hearing before the Supreme Court of Illinois.", "start": 1056.571, "stop": 1059.933, "duration": 3.36, "cleanText": [["and", "he", "ask", "this", "hearing", "before", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "illinois"]]}, {"text": "And as against disbarment, there may be censure, there may be suspension and there of course may be dismissal of charges.", "start": 1059.933, "stop": 1064.554, "duration": 4.62, "cleanText": [["and", "as", "against", "disbarment", "there", "may", "be", "censure", "there", "may", "be", "suspension", "and", "there", "of", "course", "may", "be", "dismissal", "of", "charge"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "There, they have automatic disbarment (Inaudible) --", "start": 1064.554, "stop": 1067.135, "duration": 2.58, "cleanText": [["there", "they", "have", "automatic", "disbarment", "inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm not aware of any.", "start": 1067.135, "stop": 1067.597, "duration": 0.46, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "not", "aware", "of", "any"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 1067.597, "stop": 1069.186, "duration": 1.59, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, there are no -- I'm not aware of any --", "start": 1069.186, "stop": 1072.163, "duration": 2.98, "cleanText": [["no", "there", "be", "no", "I", "be", "not", "aware", "of", "any"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "There is a rule as far as disbarment is concerned as to the defendant's proceeding.", "start": 1072.163, "stop": 1076.936, "duration": 4.77, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "a", "rule", "as", "far", "as", "disbarment", "be", "concern", "as", "to", "the", "defendant", "s", "proceeding"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 1076.936, "stop": 1078.333, "duration": 1.4, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "Excuse --", "start": 1078.333, "stop": 1078.471, "duration": 0.14, "cleanText": [["excuse"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Was this man disbarred?", "start": 1078.471, "stop": 1081.082, "duration": 2.61, "cleanText": [["be", "this", "man", "disbar"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I understand he is actively practicing at the present time.", "start": 1081.082, "stop": 1084.303, "duration": 3.22, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "understand", "he", "be", "actively", "practice", "at", "the", "present", "time"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "He just got two years in jail?", "start": 1084.303, "stop": 1086.499, "duration": 2.2, "cleanText": [["he", "just", "get", "two", "year", "in", "jail"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right.", "start": 1086.499, "stop": 1089.375, "duration": 2.88, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}, {"text": "And he's practicing.", "start": 1089.375, "stop": 1099.574, "duration": 10.2, "cleanText": [["and", "he", "be", "practice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "I wonder why if the -- if that the prime concern of the Court was that the dignity of the profession and the dignity of the Court should be upheld and he went so far as to deprive a man of a jury trial and an indictment -- a trial after an indictment, he would do this and not pursue it further and not having a disbarment proceeding.", "start": 1099.574, "stop": 1125.556, "duration": 25.98, "cleanText": [["i", "wonder", "why", "if", "the", "if", "that", "the", "prime", "concern", "of", "the", "court", "be", "that", "the", "dignity", "of", "the", "profession", "and", "the", "dignity", "of", "the", "court", "should", "be", "upheld", "and", "he", "go", "so", "far", "as", "to", "deprive", "a", "man", "of", "a", "jury", "trial", "and", "an", "indictment", "a", "trial", "after", "an", "indictment", "he", "would", "do", "this", "and", "not", "pursue", "it", "far", "and", "not", "have", "a", "disbarment", "proceeding"]]}, {"text": "Why would that be?", "start": 1125.556, "stop": 1128.352, "duration": 2.8, "cleanText": [["why", "would", "that", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "The proceedings in this case are -- there's nothing extraordinary about it.", "start": 1128.352, "stop": 1135.404, "duration": 7.05, "cleanText": [["the", "proceeding", "in", "this", "case", "be", "there", "be", "nothing", "extraordinary", "about", "it"]]}, {"text": "The committee is awaiting the outcome of the case and as a matter of fact I had a call from the Secretary about 10 days ago on the matter and that is usual in all cases.", "start": 1135.404, "stop": 1145.935, "duration": 10.53, "cleanText": [["the", "committee", "be", "await", "the", "outcome", "of", "the", "case", "and", "as", "a", "matter", "of", "fact", "i", "have", "a", "call", "from", "the", "secretary", "about", "day", "ago", "on", "the", "matter", "and", "that", "be", "usual", "in", "all", "case"]]}, {"text": "They will wait until the case is finally disposed before it is taken up by the committee acting on behalf of the Supreme Court of Illinois.", "start": 1145.935, "stop": 1152.679, "duration": 6.74, "cleanText": [["they", "will", "wait", "until", "the", "case", "be", "finally", "dispose", "before", "it", "be", "take", "up", "by", "the", "committee", "act", "on", "behalf", "of", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "illinois"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, we just had one here the other day where the Bar of Illinois moved against a person who never have had any charge against him.", "start": 1152.679, "stop": 1163.775, "duration": 11.1, "cleanText": [["well", "we", "just", "have", "one", "here", "the", "other", "day", "where", "the", "bar", "of", "illinois", "move", "against", "a", "person", "who", "never", "have", "have", "any", "charge", "against", "him"]]}, {"text": "I'm speaking of Steel Workers Union case here.", "start": 1163.775, "stop": 1168.641, "duration": 4.87, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "speak", "of", "steel", "worker", "union", "case", "here"]]}, {"text": "And we had to reverse that case but they didn't wait there for this case to be decided and the person hadn't committed any crime.", "start": 1168.641, "stop": 1179.354, "duration": 10.71, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "have", "to", "reverse", "that", "case", "but", "they", "do", "not", "wait", "there", "for", "this", "case", "to", "be", "decide", "and", "the", "person", "have", "not", "commit", "any", "crime"]]}, {"text": "But he just said that he was violating the ethics of the profession.", "start": 1179.354, "stop": 1184.214, "duration": 4.86, "cleanText": [["but", "he", "just", "say", "that", "he", "be", "violate", "the", "ethic", "of", "the", "profession"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the reason that they didn't wait there for this case to be decided is the fact that they are moving against that union and particularly the group that was servicing them with professional legal services is the very fact which gave rise of the case as I recall it.", "start": 1184.214, "stop": 1203.845, "duration": 19.63, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "reason", "that", "they", "do", "not", "wait", "there", "for", "this", "case", "to", "be", "decide", "be", "the", "fact", "that", "they", "be", "move", "against", "that", "union", "and", "particularly", "the", "group", "that", "be", "service", "them", "with", "professional", "legal", "service", "be", "the", "very", "fact", "which", "give", "rise", "of", "the", "case", "as", "i", "recall", "it"]]}, {"text": "You're talking about the --", "start": 1203.845, "stop": 1205.696, "duration": 1.85, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "talk", "about", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Wasn't the illegal practice of the law here the very thing that caused his trial for contempt?", "start": 1205.696, "stop": 1217.054, "duration": 11.36, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "the", "illegal", "practice", "of", "the", "law", "here", "the", "very", "thing", "that", "cause", "his", "trial", "for", "contempt"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would say the -- I mean you want to call that illegal practice, I would say the presentation of a fraudulent will and imposing up on the Court is the thing which brought about his contempt --", "start": 1217.054, "stop": 1224.653, "duration": 7.6, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "say", "the", "i", "mean", "you", "want", "to", "call", "that", "illegal", "practice", "i", "would", "say", "the", "presentation", "of", "a", "fraudulent", "will", "and", "impose", "up", "on", "the", "court", "be", "the", "thing", "which", "bring", "about", "his", "contempt"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, yes.", "start": 1224.653, "stop": 1225.707, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["yes", "yes"]]}, {"text": "Well, that's -- let's phrase it your way but isn't that just as important as certainly is the one we have here?", "start": 1225.707, "stop": 1234.139, "duration": 8.43, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "be", "let", "us", "phrase", "it", "your", "way", "but", "be", "not", "that", "just", "as", "important", "as", "certainly", "be", "the", "one", "we", "have", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't know what you're getting at Mr. Chief Justice, I mean the --", "start": 1234.139, "stop": 1236.353, "duration": 2.21, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know", "what", "you", "be", "get", "at", "mr", "chief", "justice", "i", "mean", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I mean this, you started your whole argument by saying that the judge was so concerned with the honorable practice of law in his court and the bar was so interested in the ethics of the profession that the Court appointed an amicus to go out and investigate this whole thing and they found that he had perpetrated this fraud upon the Court.", "start": 1236.353, "stop": 1269.704, "duration": 33.35, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "mean", "this", "you", "start", "your", "whole", "argument", "by", "say", "that", "the", "judge", "be", "so", "concerned", "with", "the", "honorable", "practice", "of", "law", "in", "his", "court", "and", "the", "bar", "be", "so", "interested", "in", "the", "ethic", "of", "the", "profession", "that", "the", "court", "appoint", "an", "amicus", "to", "go", "out", "and", "investigate", "this", "whole", "thing", "and", "they", "find", "that", "he", "have", "perpetrate", "this", "fraud", "upon", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "And now if that is true why wouldn't the bar move there when he was convicted in the court below and when he was convicted by your Supreme Court just as they did in the Steel Workers case where there wasn't any charge of fraud at all, it was just illegal practice of law.", "start": 1269.704, "stop": 1289.485, "duration": 19.78, "cleanText": [["and", "now", "if", "that", "be", "true", "why", "would", "not", "the", "bar", "move", "there", "when", "he", "be", "convict", "in", "the", "court", "below", "and", "when", "he", "be", "convict", "by", "your", "supreme", "court", "just", "as", "they", "do", "in", "the", "steel", "worker", "case", "where", "there", "be", "not", "any", "charge", "of", "fraud", "at", "all", "it", "be", "just", "illegal", "practice", "of", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I think that we have two different situations in the Steel --", "start": 1289.485, "stop": 1293.985, "duration": 4.5, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "that", "we", "have", "two", "different", "situation", "in", "the", "steel"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Of course they are different but --", "start": 1293.985, "stop": 1296.207, "duration": 2.22, "cleanText": [["of", "course", "they", "be", "different", "but"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "The Steel Workers situation gave rise to the lawsuit which eventually wound up in this Court.", "start": 1296.207, "stop": 1302.348, "duration": 6.14, "cleanText": [["the", "steel", "worker", "situation", "give", "rise", "to", "the", "lawsuit", "which", "eventually", "wind", "up", "in", "this", "court"]]}, {"text": "Whereas this case, what the Bar Association is doing and the Grievance Committee specifically is waiting for the final determination.", "start": 1302.348, "stop": 1312.812, "duration": 10.46, "cleanText": [["whereas", "this", "case", "what", "the", "bar", "association", "be", "do", "and", "the", "grievance", "committee", "specifically", "be", "wait", "for", "the", "final", "determination"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Alright, that's your answer.", "start": 1312.812, "stop": 1320.251, "duration": 7.44, "cleanText": [["alright", "that", "be", "your", "answer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yesterday afternoon when counsel for the petitioner was analyzing the fast law of the question specifically the Green and the Barnett cases and Cheff, he made a statement regarding the decision of the majority of this Court in Cheff versus Schnackenberg with which we do not agree.", "start": 1320.251, "stop": 1345.812, "duration": 25.56, "cleanText": [["yesterday", "afternoon", "when", "counsel", "for", "the", "petitioner", "be", "analyze", "the", "fast", "law", "of", "the", "question", "specifically", "the", "green", "and", "the", "barnett", "case", "and", "cheff", "he", "make", "a", "statement", "regard", "the", "decision", "of", "the", "majority", "of", "this", "court", "in", "cheff", "versus", "schnackenberg", "with", "which", "we", "do", "not", "agree"]]}, {"text": "This Court will recall that the majority in both Green and the Barnett is held at criminal contempts are not crimes, and as such, they do not fall within the purview of the -- either the Sixth Amendment or the Third Article of the Federal Constitution.", "start": 1345.812, "stop": 1363.995, "duration": 18.18, "cleanText": [["this", "court", "will", "recall", "that", "the", "majority", "in", "both", "green", "and", "the", "barnett", "be", "hold", "at", "criminal", "contempt", "be", "not", "crime", "and", "as", "such", "they", "do", "not", "fall", "within", "the", "purview", "of", "the", "either", "the", "sixth", "amendment", "or", "the", "third", "article", "of", "the", "federal", "constitution"]]}, {"text": "Then counsel moves on to the Cheff decision and suggest to this Court that an important modification was made therein by the majority and that the requirement of a jury trial in federal cases wherein sentences exceed six months has been raised to a constitutional level.", "start": 1363.995, "stop": 1387.606, "duration": 23.61, "cleanText": [["then", "counsel", "move", "on", "to", "the", "cheff", "decision", "and", "suggest", "to", "this", "court", "that", "an", "important", "modification", "be", "make", "therein", "by", "the", "majority", "and", "that", "the", "requirement", "of", "a", "jury", "trial", "in", "federal", "case", "wherein", "sentence", "exceed", "six", "month", "have", "be", "raise", "to", "a", "constitutional", "level"]]}, {"text": "We have read that that is an argument that is made by the petitioner in his brief and was repeated yesterday.", "start": 1387.606, "stop": 1394.826, "duration": 7.22, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "read", "that", "that", "be", "an", "argument", "that", "be", "make", "by", "the", "petitioner", "in", "his", "brief", "and", "be", "repeat", "yesterday"]]}, {"text": "We have disagreed with that argument and we still adhere to our position that at no time as the majority of this Court ever said either that criminal contempt was a crime and that as such it fell within the purview of the Sixth Amendment and the Third Article of the Federal Constitution.", "start": 1394.826, "stop": 1415.987, "duration": 21.16, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "disagree", "with", "that", "argument", "and", "we", "still", "adhere", "to", "our", "position", "that", "at", "no", "time", "as", "the", "majority", "of", "this", "court", "ever", "say", "either", "that", "criminal", "contempt", "be", "a", "crime", "and", "that", "as", "such", "it", "fell", "within", "the", "purview", "of", "the", "sixth", "amendment", "and", "the", "third", "article", "of", "the", "federal", "constitution"]]}, {"text": "Cheff --", "start": 1415.987, "stop": 1416.556, "duration": 0.57, "cleanText": [["cheff"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you have a statute in Illinois against contempt?", "start": 1416.556, "stop": 1419.537, "duration": 2.98, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "have", "a", "statute", "in", "illinois", "against", "contempt"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No we do not sir.", "start": 1419.537, "stop": 1420.668, "duration": 1.13, "cleanText": [["no", "we", "do", "not", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "No statute at all?", "start": 1420.668, "stop": 1421.422, "duration": 0.75, "cleanText": [["no", "statute", "at", "all"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 1421.422, "stop": 1422.387, "duration": 0.96, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "And as a matter of fact, contempts are expressly excluded from the criminal code.", "start": 1422.387, "stop": 1426.99, "duration": 4.6, "cleanText": [["and", "as", "a", "matter", "of", "fact", "contempt", "be", "expressly", "exclude", "from", "the", "criminal", "code"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is there any limit on the amount of time?", "start": 1426.99, "stop": 1429.402, "duration": 2.41, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "any", "limit", "on", "the", "amount", "of", "time"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No there is not sir.", "start": 1429.402, "stop": 1431.928, "duration": 2.53, "cleanText": [["no", "there", "be", "not", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you take the position you'd give a man 20 years without it too?", "start": 1431.928, "stop": 1435.611, "duration": 3.68, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "take", "the", "position", "you", "would", "give", "a", "man", "year", "without", "it", "too"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No I don't, I don't.", "start": 1435.611, "stop": 1437.504, "duration": 1.89, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "do", "not", "i", "do", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "But do you take five?", "start": 1437.504, "stop": 1440.505, "duration": 3, "cleanText": [["but", "do", "you", "take", "five"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "That would depend upon the case.", "start": 1440.505, "stop": 1443.071, "duration": 2.57, "cleanText": [["that", "would", "depend", "upon", "the", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Five would be alright?", "start": 1443.071, "stop": 1443.915, "duration": 0.84, "cleanText": [["five", "would", "be", "alright"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right.", "start": 1443.915, "stop": 1444.383, "duration": 0.47, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}, {"text": "But on our theory, I would have much less trouble than on theirs.", "start": 1444.383, "stop": 1448.437, "duration": 4.05, "cleanText": [["but", "on", "our", "theory", "i", "would", "have", "much", "less", "trouble", "than", "on", "theirs"]]}, {"text": "I like to take your example one step further.", "start": 1448.437, "stop": 1452.169, "duration": 3.73, "cleanText": [["i", "like", "to", "take", "your", "example", "one", "step", "far"]]}, {"text": "Let us take 20 years and let us assume that the man was given a jury trial.", "start": 1452.169, "stop": 1459.307, "duration": 7.14, "cleanText": [["let", "us", "take", "year", "and", "let", "us", "assume", "that", "the", "man", "be", "give", "a", "jury", "trial"]]}, {"text": "Could I in all sincerity and honesty stand here and defend that sentence of 20 years?", "start": 1459.307, "stop": 1464.902, "duration": 5.6, "cleanText": [["could", "i", "in", "all", "sincerity", "and", "honesty", "stand", "here", "and", "defend", "that", "sentence", "of", "year"]]}, {"text": "I think not.", "start": 1464.902, "stop": 1465.554, "duration": 0.65, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it's not this case.", "start": 1465.554, "stop": 1466.679, "duration": 1.13, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "be", "not", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "But I'll assume what's the time of the -- the maximum penalty for forgery.", "start": 1466.679, "stop": 1470.393, "duration": 3.71, "cleanText": [["but", "I", "will", "assume", "what", "be", "the", "time", "of", "the", "the", "maximum", "penalty", "for", "forgery"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "One to 14.", "start": 1470.393, "stop": 1471.725, "duration": 1.33, "cleanText": [["one", "to"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well suppose this Court gave him 15, would that be alright?", "start": 1471.725, "stop": 1477.958, "duration": 6.23, "cleanText": [["well", "suppose", "this", "court", "give", "him", "would", "that", "be", "alright"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Where a no -- no jury trial?", "start": 1477.958, "stop": 1479.59, "duration": 1.63, "cleanText": [["where", "a", "no", "no", "jury", "trial"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1479.59, "stop": 1480.129, "duration": 0.54, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would have trouble with the case but not on his theory but on the Fourteenth Amendment approach --", "start": 1480.129, "stop": 1484.881, "duration": 4.75, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "have", "trouble", "with", "the", "case", "but", "not", "on", "his", "theory", "but", "on", "the", "fourteenth", "amendment", "approach"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Couldn't I have just so much trouble --", "start": 1484.881, "stop": 1485.625, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["could", "not", "i", "have", "just", "so", "much", "trouble"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- to defend --", "start": 1485.625, "stop": 1486.619, "duration": 0.99, "cleanText": [["to", "defend"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Couldn't I have just much trouble with the two years?", "start": 1486.619, "stop": 1489.816, "duration": 3.2, "cleanText": [["could", "not", "i", "have", "just", "much", "trouble", "with", "the", "two", "year"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 1489.816, "stop": 1490.538, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["no"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why not?", "start": 1490.538, "stop": 1491.897, "duration": 1.36, "cleanText": [["why", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because then under the doctrine of basic fair play which after all is the core of the Fourteenth Amendment, this Court could as we suggested in Green.", "start": 1491.897, "stop": 1508.633, "duration": 16.74, "cleanText": [["because", "then", "under", "the", "doctrine", "of", "basic", "fair", "play", "which", "after", "all", "be", "the", "core", "of", "the", "fourteenth", "amendment", "this", "court", "could", "as", "we", "suggest", "in", "green"]]}, {"text": "Examine whether or not the trial judge here had abused his discretion.", "start": 1508.633, "stop": 1514.763, "duration": 6.13, "cleanText": [["examine", "whether", "or", "not", "the", "trial", "judge", "here", "have", "abuse", "his", "discretion"]]}, {"text": "It is our view that after this Court examines the evidence in the context it will find that the discretion was not abused in sentencing the gentleman with two years.", "start": 1514.763, "stop": 1530.903, "duration": 16.14, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "our", "view", "that", "after", "this", "court", "examine", "the", "evidence", "in", "the", "context", "it", "will", "find", "that", "the", "discretion", "be", "not", "abuse", "in", "sentence", "the", "gentleman", "with", "two", "year"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "What is the situation in Illinois with respect to entitlement to jury trial?", "start": 1530.903, "stop": 1536.644, "duration": 5.74, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "the", "situation", "in", "illinois", "with", "respect", "to", "entitlement", "to", "jury", "trial"]]}, {"text": "Is there a dividing line, a misdemeanor -- what do you call it under your Illinois system?", "start": 1536.644, "stop": 1543.852, "duration": 7.21, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "a", "dividing", "line", "a", "misdemeanor", "what", "do", "you", "call", "it", "under", "your", "illinois", "system"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "We have a -- we do not have a petty offense.", "start": 1543.852, "stop": 1546.065, "duration": 2.21, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "a", "we", "do", "not", "have", "a", "petty", "offense"]]}, {"text": "We have a misdemeanor which is determined by the amount of punishment that is anything a year under (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 1546.065, "stop": 1550.881, "duration": 4.82, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "a", "misdemeanor", "which", "be", "determine", "by", "the", "amount", "of", "punishment", "that", "be", "anything", "a", "year", "under", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "A -- one year or under?", "start": 1550.881, "stop": 1552.503, "duration": 1.62, "cleanText": [["a", "one", "year", "or", "under"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right.", "start": 1552.503, "stop": 1553.78, "duration": 1.28, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "And there, you're not entitled to a jury.", "start": 1553.78, "stop": 1555.847, "duration": 2.07, "cleanText": [["and", "there", "you", "be", "not", "entitle", "to", "a", "jury"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, but they are -- accord a jury trials, when they request them, they accord a jury trial.", "start": 1555.847, "stop": 1560.161, "duration": 4.31, "cleanText": [["no", "but", "they", "be", "accord", "a", "jury", "trial", "when", "they", "request", "them", "they", "accord", "a", "jury", "trial"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "On request, you can --", "start": 1560.161, "stop": 1560.986, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["on", "request", "you", "can"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right.", "start": 1560.986, "stop": 1561.147, "duration": 0.16, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- get one.", "start": 1561.147, "stop": 1561.996, "duration": 0.85, "cleanText": [["get", "one"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right.", "start": 1561.996, "stop": 1562.551, "duration": 0.55, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is that in any misdemeanor?", "start": 1562.551, "stop": 1566.295, "duration": 3.74, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "in", "any", "misdemeanor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "As far as I know, yes.", "start": 1566.295, "stop": 1568.268, "duration": 1.97, "cleanText": [["as", "far", "as", "i", "know", "yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "I see.", "start": 1568.268, "stop": 1568.76, "duration": 0.49, "cleanText": [["i", "see"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "The jury courts in the police level.", "start": 1568.76, "stop": 1571.022, "duration": 2.26, "cleanText": [["the", "jury", "court", "in", "the", "police", "level"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "So that what you have here is that as a system -- general system of law of judicial administration and the way in Illinois of which anybody who was tried for a misdemeanor meaning and offense in which the maximum punishment is a year is not automatically entitled a jury trial to make -- get it on request.", "start": 1571.022, "stop": 1594.361, "duration": 23.34, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "what", "you", "have", "here", "be", "that", "as", "a", "system", "general", "system", "of", "law", "of", "judicial", "administration", "and", "the", "way", "in", "illinois", "of", "which", "anybody", "who", "be", "try", "for", "a", "misdemeanor", "meaning", "and", "offense", "in", "which", "the", "maximum", "punishment", "be", "a", "year", "be", "not", "automatically", "entitle", "a", "jury", "trial", "to", "make", "get", "it", "on", "request"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "On request.", "start": 1594.361, "stop": 1595.259, "duration": 0.9, "cleanText": [["on", "request"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "But if he is tried for felony meaning where the punishment is at the excess of a year or maybe an excess of a year is entitled a jury trial.", "start": 1595.259, "stop": 1605.075, "duration": 9.82, "cleanText": [["but", "if", "he", "be", "try", "for", "felony", "meaning", "where", "the", "punishment", "be", "at", "the", "excess", "of", "a", "year", "or", "maybe", "an", "excess", "of", "a", "year", "be", "entitle", "a", "jury", "trial"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 1605.075, "stop": 1606.049, "duration": 0.97, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "He can either request it or waive it.", "start": 1606.049, "stop": 1608.756, "duration": 2.71, "cleanText": [["he", "can", "either", "request", "it", "or", "waive", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do I understand you to say that in Illinois it's discretionary with the Court as to whether a man --", "start": 1608.756, "stop": 1616.398, "duration": 7.64, "cleanText": [["do", "i", "understand", "you", "to", "say", "that", "in", "illinois", "it", "be", "discretionary", "with", "the", "court", "as", "to", "whether", "a", "man"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No it is not.", "start": 1616.398, "stop": 1616.581, "duration": 0.18, "cleanText": [["no", "it", "be", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- be given a jury in a misdemeanor case or does he have the right to demand a jury trial if he wants one?", "start": 1616.581, "stop": 1624.103, "duration": 7.52, "cleanText": [["be", "give", "a", "jury", "in", "a", "misdemeanor", "case", "or", "do", "he", "have", "the", "right", "to", "demand", "a", "jury", "trial", "if", "he", "want", "one"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "As I understand it sir, he has the right to demand a jury trial.", "start": 1624.103, "stop": 1626.844, "duration": 2.74, "cleanText": [["as", "i", "understand", "it", "sir", "he", "have", "the", "right", "to", "demand", "a", "jury", "trial"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "And he is entitled to have it?", "start": 1626.844, "stop": 1628.717, "duration": 1.87, "cleanText": [["and", "he", "be", "entitle", "to", "have", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right.", "start": 1628.717, "stop": 1629.254, "duration": 0.54, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "In a misdemeanor case?", "start": 1629.254, "stop": 1630.54, "duration": 1.29, "cleanText": [["in", "a", "misdemeanor", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "And he receives it.", "start": 1630.54, "stop": 1631.839, "duration": 1.3, "cleanText": [["and", "he", "receive", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that's a little different, isn't it --", "start": 1631.839, "stop": 1633.358, "duration": 1.52, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "be", "a", "little", "different", "be", "not", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1633.358, "stop": 1633.395, "duration": 0.04, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- from what you just said?", "start": 1633.395, "stop": 1635.432, "duration": 2.04, "cleanText": [["from", "what", "you", "just", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think I said the same thing to Mr. Justice Fortas.", "start": 1635.432, "stop": 1637.742, "duration": 2.31, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "i", "say", "the", "same", "thing", "to", "mr", "justice", "fortas"]]}, {"text": "I'm sorry.", "start": 1637.742, "stop": 1637.768, "duration": 0.03, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sorry"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, no.", "start": 1637.768, "stop": 1638.783, "duration": 1.01, "cleanText": [["oh", "no"]]}, {"text": "You said he may have one, but it's different, he's entitled to one if he wants it.", "start": 1638.783, "stop": 1644.7, "duration": 5.92, "cleanText": [["you", "say", "he", "may", "have", "one", "but", "it", "be", "different", "he", "be", "entitle", "to", "one", "if", "he", "want", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, when I said he may, what I meant was that he can request it and then receive it.", "start": 1644.7, "stop": 1650.184, "duration": 5.48, "cleanText": [["well", "when", "i", "say", "he", "may", "what", "i", "meant", "be", "that", "he", "can", "request", "it", "and", "then", "receive", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you permit defendants to be tried by -- without a jury in felony cases?", "start": 1650.184, "stop": 1657.162, "duration": 6.98, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "permit", "defendant", "to", "be", "try", "by", "without", "a", "jury", "in", "felony", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, yes but of course the waiver --", "start": 1657.162, "stop": 1658.238, "duration": 1.08, "cleanText": [["oh", "yes", "but", "of", "course", "the", "waiver"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Then what's the difference?", "start": 1658.238, "stop": 1659.62, "duration": 1.38, "cleanText": [["then", "what", "be", "the", "difference"]]}, {"text": "He demands it from both of them, he gets it.", "start": 1659.62, "stop": 1663.601, "duration": 3.98, "cleanText": [["he", "demand", "it", "from", "both", "of", "them", "he", "get", "it"]]}, {"text": "He demands a felony case, he gets it.", "start": 1663.601, "stop": 1665.817, "duration": 2.22, "cleanText": [["he", "demand", "a", "felony", "case", "he", "get", "it"]]}, {"text": "If he demands a misdemeanor, he gets it.", "start": 1665.817, "stop": 1668.09, "duration": 2.27, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "demand", "a", "misdemeanor", "he", "get", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 1668.09, "stop": 1668.895, "duration": 0.81, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, what's the difference?", "start": 1668.895, "stop": 1669.91, "duration": 1.02, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "be", "the", "difference"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "None.", "start": 1669.91, "stop": 1671.001, "duration": 1.09, "cleanText": [["none"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I just thought the import of what you said to Justice Fortas was a little different as between --", "start": 1671.001, "stop": 1676.509, "duration": 5.51, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "just", "think", "the", "import", "of", "what", "you", "say", "to", "justice", "fortas", "be", "a", "little", "different", "as", "between"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I didn't intend to setup any distinction.", "start": 1676.509, "stop": 1678.31, "duration": 1.8, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "do", "not", "intend", "to", "setup", "any", "distinction"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Very well.", "start": 1678.31, "stop": 1678.664, "duration": 0.35, "cleanText": [["very", "well"]]}, {"text": "I'm mistaken then.", "start": 1678.664, "stop": 1684.578, "duration": 5.91, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "mistaken", "then"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "The fact here is that in Illinois, any time you do to a man has a consequence of some of this conduct.", "start": 1684.578, "stop": 1695.391, "duration": 10.81, "cleanText": [["the", "fact", "here", "be", "that", "in", "illinois", "any", "time", "you", "do", "to", "a", "man", "have", "a", "consequence", "of", "some", "of", "this", "conduct"]]}, {"text": "What was done in this case to a man where all admit that the punishment of disbarment was the most serious things that can appear, you take that one clash of cases out and deny him a jury trial?", "start": 1695.391, "stop": 1716.944, "duration": 21.55, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "do", "in", "this", "case", "to", "a", "man", "where", "all", "admit", "that", "the", "punishment", "of", "disbarment", "be", "the", "most", "serious", "thing", "that", "can", "appear", "you", "take", "that", "one", "clash", "of", "case", "out", "and", "deny", "him", "a", "jury", "trial"]]}, {"text": "That's the fact, isn't it?", "start": 1716.944, "stop": 1718.959, "duration": 2.02, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "fact", "be", "not", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "I didn't -- I'm sorry sir, I didn't hear the first part of your observation.", "start": 1718.959, "stop": 1726.765, "duration": 7.81, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "I", "be", "sorry", "sir", "i", "do", "not", "hear", "the", "first", "part", "of", "your", "observation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "He was not disbarred here of course --", "start": 1726.765, "stop": 1728.747, "duration": 1.98, "cleanText": [["he", "be", "not", "disbar", "here", "of", "course"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No he's not.", "start": 1728.747, "stop": 1728.776, "duration": 0.03, "cleanText": [["no", "he", "be", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- but he could be.", "start": 1728.776, "stop": 1730.002, "duration": 1.23, "cleanText": [["but", "he", "could", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "He could be, yes.", "start": 1730.002, "stop": 1730.956, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["he", "could", "be", "yes"]]}, {"text": "That would be dependent upon the judgment of the Supreme Court of Illinois in their disciplinary proceedings.", "start": 1730.956, "stop": 1736.121, "duration": 5.17, "cleanText": [["that", "would", "be", "dependent", "upon", "the", "judgment", "of", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "illinois", "in", "their", "disciplinary", "proceeding"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "But if you call it a misdemeanor or a felony -- you name a misdemeanor or a felony, he's entitled to a trial by jury.", "start": 1736.121, "stop": 1743.93, "duration": 7.81, "cleanText": [["but", "if", "you", "call", "it", "a", "misdemeanor", "or", "a", "felony", "you", "name", "a", "misdemeanor", "or", "a", "felony", "he", "be", "entitle", "to", "a", "trial", "by", "jury"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "If he requested it, he would get it.", "start": 1743.93, "stop": 1745.532, "duration": 1.6, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "request", "it", "he", "would", "get", "it"]]}, {"text": "Yes.", "start": 1745.532, "stop": 1750.352, "duration": 4.82, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's a kind of anachronism that's gone out of history, isn't it?", "start": 1750.352, "stop": 1756.167, "duration": 5.81, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "a", "kind", "of", "anachronism", "that", "be", "go", "out", "of", "history", "be", "not", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, whether we call it anachronism --", "start": 1756.167, "stop": 1758.385, "duration": 2.22, "cleanText": [["well", "whether", "we", "call", "it", "anachronism"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, but that's may be the wrong thing.", "start": 1758.385, "stop": 1760.211, "duration": 1.83, "cleanText": [["yes", "but", "that", "be", "may", "be", "the", "wrong", "thing"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, but the fact of the matter is that contempt has always been regarded.", "start": 1760.211, "stop": 1768.204, "duration": 7.99, "cleanText": [["yes", "but", "the", "fact", "of", "the", "matter", "be", "that", "contempt", "have", "always", "be", "regard"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, by some.", "start": 1768.204, "stop": 1770.42, "duration": 2.22, "cleanText": [["well", "by", "some"]]}, {"text": "Has always been a scrambling position of that by the judiciary which has been contested most frequently by the legislative mind.", "start": 1770.42, "stop": 1779.895, "duration": 9.47, "cleanText": [["have", "always", "be", "a", "scramble", "position", "of", "that", "by", "the", "judiciary", "which", "have", "be", "contest", "most", "frequently", "by", "the", "legislative", "mind"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "There -- I will concede that there is difficulty on the part of someone to accept the prevailing view that it is sui generis and does enjoy this unique position.", "start": 1779.895, "stop": 1790.391, "duration": 10.5, "cleanText": [["there", "i", "will", "concede", "that", "there", "be", "difficulty", "on", "the", "part", "of", "someone", "to", "accept", "the", "prevailing", "view", "that", "it", "be", "sui", "generis", "and", "do", "enjoy", "this", "unique", "position"]]}, {"text": "There are as you well know Mr. Justice Black, those who feel that it should be equated to the status of a crime and that all the privileges should --", "start": 1790.391, "stop": 1799.434, "duration": 9.04, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "as", "you", "well", "know", "mr", "justice", "black", "those", "who", "feel", "that", "it", "should", "be", "equate", "to", "the", "status", "of", "a", "crime", "and", "that", "all", "the", "privilege", "should"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "It feel that he should be treated as what it is with that regard to its name?", "start": 1799.434, "stop": 1811.125, "duration": 11.69, "cleanText": [["it", "feel", "that", "he", "should", "be", "treat", "as", "what", "it", "be", "with", "that", "regard", "to", "its", "name"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Hladis, does your Illinois constitution have a jury trial probation?", "start": 1811.125, "stop": 1816.066, "duration": 4.94, "cleanText": [["mr", "hladis", "do", "your", "illinois", "constitution", "have", "a", "jury", "trial", "probation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1816.066, "stop": 1816.62, "duration": 0.55, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "What does it say?", "start": 1816.62, "stop": 1823.416, "duration": 6.8, "cleanText": [["what", "do", "it", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "Substantially, what the federal constitution says that the -- in crimes that the people are entitled to a jury trial.", "start": 1823.416, "stop": 1834.55, "duration": 11.13, "cleanText": [["substantially", "what", "the", "federal", "constitution", "say", "that", "the", "in", "crime", "that", "the", "people", "be", "entitle", "to", "a", "jury", "trial"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Does it make any distinction between misdemeanors and felonies?", "start": 1834.55, "stop": 1837.588, "duration": 3.04, "cleanText": [["do", "it", "make", "any", "distinction", "between", "misdemeanor", "and", "felony"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "As far as I recall, no sir.", "start": 1837.588, "stop": 1839.564, "duration": 1.98, "cleanText": [["as", "far", "as", "i", "recall", "no", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "And does your judge made law make any distinction between it.", "start": 1839.564, "stop": 1845.893, "duration": 6.33, "cleanText": [["and", "do", "your", "judge", "make", "law", "make", "any", "distinction", "between", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Edward J. Hladis", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 1845.893, "stop": 1853.869, "duration": 7.98, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "I see my time is up, gentlemen.", "start": 1853.869, "stop": 1855.535, "duration": 1.67, "cleanText": [["i", "see", "my", "time", "be", "up", "gentleman"]]}, {"text": "Thank you very much.", "start": 1855.535, "stop": 1860.654, "duration": 5.12, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "very", "much"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, may it please the Court.", "start": 1860.654, "stop": 1865.654, "duration": 5, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "In response to Chief Justice's last question we have set forth the exact constitutional provisions of the Illinois statute on page 2 of our original brief in this Court.", "start": 1865.654, "stop": 1878.664, "duration": 13.01, "cleanText": [["in", "response", "to", "chief", "justice", "s", "last", "question", "we", "have", "set", "forth", "the", "exact", "constitutional", "provision", "of", "the", "illinois", "statute", "on", "page", "of", "our", "original", "brief", "in", "this", "court"]]}, {"text": "There are two Sections really which covered in Illinois.", "start": 1878.664, "stop": 1882.474, "duration": 3.81, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "two", "section", "really", "which", "cover", "in", "illinois"]]}, {"text": "Article II, Section 5 provides that the right of trial by jury as here before enjoined shall remain in (Inaudible).", "start": 1882.474, "stop": 1892.094, "duration": 9.62, "cleanText": [["article", "ii", "section", "provide", "that", "the", "right", "of", "trial", "by", "jury", "as", "here", "before", "enjoin", "shall", "remain", "in", "inaudible"]]}, {"text": "Article II, Section 9 says, In all criminal prosecutions, the accused shall have the right to a speedy public trial by an impartial jury.", "start": 1892.094, "stop": 1903.318, "duration": 11.22, "cleanText": [["article", "ii", "section", "say", "in", "all", "criminal", "prosecution", "the", "accuse", "shall", "have", "the", "right", "to", "a", "speedy", "public", "trial", "by", "an", "impartial", "jury"]]}, {"text": "Nevertheless in Illinois over the years, there has grown up a body of law which I frankly concedes to the Court which has consistently withheld from criminal contender's a right to trial by a jury which I analyzed incidentally in my brief before the Supreme Court of the State to show that it grew as somewhat in topsy like fashion and was based upon a forced premise which originated in a pure civil contempt case where of course it's quite proper to deny trials by jury.", "start": 1903.318, "stop": 1936.364, "duration": 33.05, "cleanText": [["nevertheless", "in", "illinois", "over", "the", "year", "there", "have", "grow", "up", "a", "body", "of", "law", "which", "i", "frankly", "concedes", "to", "the", "court", "which", "have", "consistently", "withhold", "from", "criminal", "contender", "s", "a", "right", "to", "trial", "by", "a", "jury", "which", "i", "analyze", "incidentally", "in", "my", "brief", "before", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "the", "state", "to", "show", "that", "it", "grow", "as", "somewhat", "in", "topsy", "like", "fashion", "and", "be", "base", "upon", "a", "force", "premise", "which", "originate", "in", "a", "pure", "civil", "contempt", "case", "where", "of", "course", "it", "be", "quite", "proper", "to", "deny", "trial", "by", "jury"]]}, {"text": "And based upon that fragile basis, they grew with Illinois the body of law to which I have just referred and to which the Illinois Supreme Court still adheres in this case dismissing the holding of this Court in Cheff v. Schnackenberg with -- I use to word advisedly to stay in almost making only passing reference to it.", "start": 1936.364, "stop": 1961.01, "duration": 24.65, "cleanText": [["and", "base", "upon", "that", "fragile", "basis", "they", "grow", "with", "illinois", "the", "body", "of", "law", "to", "which", "i", "have", "just", "refer", "and", "to", "which", "the", "illinois", "supreme", "court", "still", "adhere", "in", "this", "case", "dismiss", "the", "holding", "of", "this", "court", "in", "cheff", "v", "schnackenberg", "with", "i", "use", "to", "word", "advisedly", "to", "stay", "in", "almost", "make", "only", "pass", "reference", "to", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Cheff and Schnackenberg is a federal case and so far at least, so far the Illinois practice has been identical to the practice through and through both the federal cases and state cases by this Court and (Inaudilbe).", "start": 1961.01, "stop": 1981.673, "duration": 20.66, "cleanText": [["well", "cheff", "and", "schnackenberg", "be", "a", "federal", "case", "and", "so", "far", "at", "least", "so", "far", "the", "illinois", "practice", "have", "be", "identical", "to", "the", "practice", "through", "and", "through", "both", "the", "federal", "case", "and", "state", "case", "by", "this", "court", "and", "inaudilbe"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, I would say --", "start": 1981.673, "stop": 1982.83, "duration": 1.16, "cleanText": [["yes", "i", "would", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Nothing unusual about what Illinois has done.", "start": 1982.83, "stop": 1985.304, "duration": 2.47, "cleanText": [["nothing", "unusual", "about", "what", "illinois", "have", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "You're quite right Mr. Justice Harlan.", "start": 1985.304, "stop": 1986.845, "duration": 1.54, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "quite", "right", "mr", "justice", "harlan"]]}, {"text": "Up until now, they have adhere to Green and Barnett and in fact rely upon it again in their decision in this case, the case at bar.", "start": 1986.845, "stop": 1999.263, "duration": 12.42, "cleanText": [["up", "until", "now", "they", "have", "adhere", "to", "green", "and", "barnett", "and", "in", "fact", "rely", "upon", "it", "again", "in", "their", "decision", "in", "this", "case", "the", "case", "at", "bar"]]}, {"text": "And we're critical of that of course when we say that they have failed to recognize the important modifications in Green and Barnett as now written by this Court in Cheff.", "start": 1999.263, "stop": 2011.462, "duration": 12.2, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "be", "critical", "of", "that", "of", "course", "when", "we", "say", "that", "they", "have", "fail", "to", "recognize", "the", "important", "modification", "in", "green", "and", "barnett", "as", "now", "write", "by", "this", "court", "in", "cheff"]]}, {"text": "Incidentally, I revisited Green after the colloquy I had with the Court yesterday and I am able to say that the Court that there was no criminal statute involved in Green in effect at the time of the alleged contemptuous acts.", "start": 2011.462, "stop": 2030.38, "duration": 18.92, "cleanText": [["incidentally", "i", "revisit", "green", "after", "the", "colloquy", "i", "have", "with", "the", "court", "yesterday", "and", "i", "be", "able", "to", "say", "that", "the", "court", "that", "there", "be", "no", "criminal", "statute", "involve", "in", "green", "in", "effect", "at", "the", "time", "of", "the", "allege", "contemptuous", "act"]]}, {"text": "The defendant there had been convicted of a crime and jumped and he refused to obey an order.", "start": 2030.38, "stop": 2039.189, "duration": 8.81, "cleanText": [["the", "defendant", "there", "have", "be", "convict", "of", "a", "crime", "and", "jump", "and", "he", "refuse", "to", "obey", "an", "order"]]}, {"text": "As he jumped down, he refused to obey an order to surrender and he was tried on contempt for disobedience of that order.", "start": 2039.189, "stop": 2047.444, "duration": 8.25, "cleanText": [["as", "he", "jump", "down", "he", "refuse", "to", "obey", "an", "order", "to", "surrender", "and", "he", "be", "try", "on", "contempt", "for", "disobedience", "of", "that", "order"]]}, {"text": "And as Mr. Justice Harlan wrote in the majority opinion of that case, he observed that the bail jumping statute had not yet been enacted.", "start": 2047.444, "stop": 2056.665, "duration": 9.22, "cleanText": [["and", "as", "mr", "justice", "harlan", "write", "in", "the", "majority", "opinion", "of", "that", "case", "he", "observe", "that", "the", "bail", "jump", "statute", "have", "not", "yet", "be", "enact"]]}, {"text": "It had been enacted in 1990 -- in 1954 whereas the contemptuous acts -- the acts complained off occurred in 1951 and passed it on to the Court because I received the impression probably incorrectly yesterday that there was a contention that there was a criminal statute at to time.One other thing, counsel refers to the fact that in the Supreme Court of the State of Illinois we conceded guilt.", "start": 2056.665, "stop": 2089.04, "duration": 32.38, "cleanText": [["it", "have", "be", "enact", "in", "in", "whereas", "the", "contemptuous", "act", "the", "act", "complain", "off", "occur", "in", "and", "pass", "it", "on", "to", "the", "court", "because", "i", "receive", "the", "impression", "probably", "incorrectly", "yesterday", "that", "there", "be", "a", "contention", "that", "there", "be", "a", "criminal", "statute", "at", "to", "timeone", "other", "thing", "counsel", "refers", "to", "the", "fact", "that", "in", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "the", "state", "of", "illinois", "we", "concede", "guilt"]]}, {"text": "And Mr. Justice White's observation on it of course I thought was quite correct.", "start": 2089.04, "stop": 2094.002, "duration": 4.96, "cleanText": [["and", "mr", "justice", "white", "s", "observation", "on", "it", "of", "course", "i", "think", "be", "quite", "correct"]]}, {"text": "That is that we contested right from the very beginning of course by reason of our plea of not guilty.", "start": 2094.002, "stop": 2100.127, "duration": 6.13, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "that", "we", "contest", "right", "from", "the", "very", "beginning", "of", "course", "by", "reason", "of", "our", "plea", "of", "not", "guilty"]]}, {"text": "But when we got to the Supreme Court of the State upon the record, I did not plan to engage in a long argument based upon the sufficiency of the evidence since the trial judge waived the evidence.", "start": 2100.127, "stop": 2113.824, "duration": 13.7, "cleanText": [["but", "when", "we", "get", "to", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "the", "state", "upon", "the", "record", "i", "do", "not", "plan", "to", "engage", "in", "a", "long", "argument", "base", "upon", "the", "sufficiency", "of", "the", "evidence", "since", "the", "trial", "judge", "waive", "the", "evidence"]]}, {"text": "He was the trier of the fact, he waived the evidence, he judged the credibility of the witnesses and so on.", "start": 2113.824, "stop": 2119.937, "duration": 6.11, "cleanText": [["he", "be", "the", "trier", "of", "the", "fact", "he", "waive", "the", "evidence", "he", "judge", "the", "credibility", "of", "the", "witness", "and", "so", "on"]]}, {"text": "Oh, I did not, however concede in the Supreme Court of the State that there was just no other side to it.", "start": 2119.937, "stop": 2126.539, "duration": 6.6, "cleanText": [["oh", "i", "do", "not", "however", "concede", "in", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "the", "state", "that", "there", "be", "just", "no", "other", "side", "to", "it"]]}, {"text": "I said incidentally in brief that the page referred to by Mr. Hladis, in a footnote that the defendant concedes that the people's evidence when viewed on appeal as it must be viewed on appeal in the light most favorable to the people that the evidence was sufficient to support the Court's judgment because it's quite true.", "start": 2126.539, "stop": 2149.324, "duration": 22.78, "cleanText": [["i", "say", "incidentally", "in", "brief", "that", "the", "page", "refer", "to", "by", "mr", "hladis", "in", "a", "footnote", "that", "the", "defendant", "concede", "that", "the", "people", "s", "evidence", "when", "view", "on", "appeal", "as", "it", "must", "be", "view", "on", "appeal", "in", "the", "light", "most", "favorable", "to", "the", "people", "that", "the", "evidence", "be", "sufficient", "to", "support", "the", "court", "s", "judgment", "because", "it", "be", "quite", "true"]]}, {"text": "And I also said in our brief here on page 2, I said the petitioner did not challenge the sufficiency of the evidence of the Illinois Supreme Court in view of the rule prevailing in that state that a verdict will not be disturbed on appeal when there is any evidence which when taken with its intendments most favorable to an appellee tends to prove the essential allegations of the complaint.", "start": 2149.324, "stop": 2178.558, "duration": 29.23, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "also", "say", "in", "our", "brief", "here", "on", "page", "i", "say", "the", "petitioner", "do", "not", "challenge", "the", "sufficiency", "of", "the", "evidence", "of", "the", "illinois", "supreme", "court", "in", "view", "of", "the", "rule", "prevail", "in", "that", "state", "that", "a", "verdict", "will", "not", "be", "disturb", "on", "appeal", "when", "there", "be", "any", "evidence", "which", "when", "take", "with", "its", "intendments", "most", "favorable", "to", "an", "appellee", "tends", "to", "prove", "the", "essential", "allegation", "of", "the", "complaint"]]}, {"text": "I would, I submit most respectfully to the Court that a complete waste of time to me on this record to go up and say that our psychiatrist should have been believed, the psychiatric evidence established.", "start": 2178.558, "stop": 2190.126, "duration": 11.57, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "i", "submit", "most", "respectfully", "to", "the", "court", "that", "a", "complete", "waste", "of", "time", "to", "me", "on", "this", "record", "to", "go", "up", "and", "say", "that", "our", "psychiatrist", "should", "have", "be", "believe", "the", "psychiatric", "evidence", "establish"]]}, {"text": "As Mr. Justice Brennan says that the malevolent intent necessary to a criminal contempt was not shown but we had an attorney who represented an adversary party in the trial court proceedings testified in the trial.", "start": 2190.126, "stop": 2207.081, "duration": 16.95, "cleanText": [["as", "mr", "justice", "brennan", "say", "that", "the", "malevolent", "intent", "necessary", "to", "a", "criminal", "contempt", "be", "not", "show", "but", "we", "have", "an", "attorney", "who", "represent", "an", "adversary", "party", "in", "the", "trial", "court", "proceeding", "testify", "in", "the", "trial"]]}, {"text": "A cross-examination that when he thought with the petitioner prior to the time that he would open or present the spurious will, he was convinced and this is in the record that the petitioner did not realize the involvements he was getting into.", "start": 2207.081, "stop": 2224.244, "duration": 17.16, "cleanText": [["a", "cross", "examination", "that", "when", "he", "think", "with", "the", "petitioner", "prior", "to", "the", "time", "that", "he", "would", "open", "or", "present", "the", "spurious", "will", "he", "be", "convince", "and", "this", "be", "in", "the", "record", "that", "the", "petitioner", "do", "not", "realize", "the", "involvement", "he", "be", "get", "into"]]}, {"text": "It did not have the mind, my own language to understand his predicament at that time.", "start": 2224.244, "stop": 2230.277, "duration": 6.03, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "have", "the", "mind", "my", "own", "language", "to", "understand", "his", "predicament", "at", "that", "time"]]}, {"text": "All of which within, but this was disregarded of course by the trial court.", "start": 2230.277, "stop": 2236.067, "duration": 5.79, "cleanText": [["all", "of", "which", "within", "but", "this", "be", "disregard", "of", "course", "by", "the", "trial", "court"]]}, {"text": "And I point out although it -- only been touched on briefly by Mr. Hladis that one of the complications in this case is this amicus curiae secret report which we have referred to as the fink report since the amicus curiae was a Mr. Fink.", "start": 2236.067, "stop": 2257.098, "duration": 21.03, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "point", "out", "although", "it", "only", "be", "touch", "on", "briefly", "by", "mr", "hladis", "that", "one", "of", "the", "complication", "in", "this", "case", "be", "this", "amicus", "curiae", "secret", "report", "which", "we", "have", "refer", "to", "as", "the", "fink", "report", "since", "the", "amicus", "curia", "be", "a", "mr", "fink"]]}, {"text": "I like to think that the word is descriptive incidentally by the card here but in any event, the -- that report found its way into the trial court's chambers.", "start": 2257.098, "stop": 2267.448, "duration": 10.35, "cleanText": [["i", "like", "to", "think", "that", "the", "word", "be", "descriptive", "incidentally", "by", "the", "card", "here", "but", "in", "any", "event", "the", "that", "report", "find", "its", "way", "into", "the", "trial", "court", "s", "chamber"]]}, {"text": "It was viewed there in camera and he has refused to make it part of the record here in this case although we asked for an order on it.", "start": 2267.448, "stop": 2276.94, "duration": 9.49, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "view", "there", "in", "camera", "and", "he", "have", "refuse", "to", "make", "it", "part", "of", "the", "record", "here", "in", "this", "case", "although", "we", "ask", "for", "an", "order", "on", "it"]]}, {"text": "So it still remains secret.", "start": 2276.94, "stop": 2278.502, "duration": 1.56, "cleanText": [["so", "it", "still", "remain", "secret"]]}, {"text": "We don't know what's in it.", "start": 2278.502, "stop": 2280.238, "duration": 1.74, "cleanText": [["we", "do", "not", "know", "what", "be", "in", "it"]]}, {"text": "And it compounds the fact that we would deny the jury.", "start": 2280.238, "stop": 2286.076, "duration": 5.84, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "compound", "the", "fact", "that", "we", "would", "deny", "the", "jury"]]}, {"text": "Had we had a jury would be bad enough for the trial court to have such a report anyway if you can visualize a Federal District Court judge with FBI reports at his chambers before he proceeds to a trial -- a case if it's so much similar to this.", "start": 2286.076, "stop": 2300.709, "duration": 14.63, "cleanText": [["have", "we", "have", "a", "jury", "would", "be", "bad", "enough", "for", "the", "trial", "court", "to", "have", "such", "a", "report", "anyway", "if", "you", "can", "visualize", "a", "federal", "district", "court", "judge", "with", "fbi", "report", "at", "his", "chamber", "before", "he", "proceed", "to", "a", "trial", "a", "case", "if", "it", "be", "so", "much", "similar", "to", "this"]]}, {"text": "But where the trier of the fact is that person and I think additional emphasis should be given to (Inaudible) and that is one of the errors we complained about.", "start": 2300.709, "stop": 2309.91, "duration": 9.2, "cleanText": [["but", "where", "the", "trier", "of", "the", "fact", "be", "that", "person", "and", "i", "think", "additional", "emphasis", "should", "be", "give", "to", "inaudible", "and", "that", "be", "one", "of", "the", "error", "we", "complain", "about"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would you mind telling us how this amicus report came into being please.", "start": 2309.91, "stop": 2315.461, "duration": 5.55, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "mind", "tell", "us", "how", "this", "amicus", "report", "come", "into", "be", "please"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes sir.", "start": 2315.461, "stop": 2316.986, "duration": 1.53, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}, {"text": "The proceeding originally began in the probate court of Cook County upon the presentation of a petition to the Court by -- as under a prior will who would have been out under the spurious will.", "start": 2316.986, "stop": 2333.502, "duration": 16.52, "cleanText": [["the", "proceed", "originally", "begin", "in", "the", "probate", "court", "of", "cook", "county", "upon", "the", "presentation", "of", "a", "petition", "to", "the", "court", "by", "as", "under", "a", "prior", "will", "who", "would", "have", "be", "out", "under", "the", "spurious", "will"]]}, {"text": "In it, they alleged and it's in the record incidentally with -- and you can refer to it at the proper time.", "start": 2333.502, "stop": 2338.707, "duration": 5.2, "cleanText": [["in", "it", "they", "allege", "and", "it", "be", "in", "the", "record", "incidentally", "with", "and", "you", "can", "refer", "to", "it", "at", "the", "proper", "time"]]}, {"text": "In it, they alleged that they sought fraud was being perpetrated upon the Court by the presentation of this other will and they specifically asked the trial court for the appointment of an amicus curiae for the purpose of investigating and prosecuting if necessary the fraud involved.", "start": 2338.707, "stop": 2359.445, "duration": 20.74, "cleanText": [["in", "it", "they", "allege", "that", "they", "seek", "fraud", "be", "be", "perpetrate", "upon", "the", "court", "by", "the", "presentation", "of", "this", "other", "will", "and", "they", "specifically", "ask", "the", "trial", "court", "for", "the", "appointment", "of", "an", "amicus", "curia", "for", "the", "purpose", "of", "investigate", "and", "prosecute", "if", "necessary", "the", "fraud", "involve"]]}, {"text": "The trial court read at that motion and appointed Mr. Fink.", "start": 2359.445, "stop": 2364.109, "duration": 4.66, "cleanText": [["the", "trial", "court", "read", "at", "that", "motion", "and", "appoint", "mr", "fink"]]}, {"text": "Thereafter, I think within approximately 60 or 90 days, the trial court entered an order upon the amicus curiae requiring him to file his report with the trial court and such a report was filed and was held in camera by the Court.", "start": 2364.109, "stop": 2383.462, "duration": 19.35, "cleanText": [["thereafter", "i", "think", "within", "approximately", "or", "day", "the", "trial", "court", "enter", "an", "order", "upon", "the", "amicus", "curia", "require", "him", "to", "file", "his", "report", "with", "the", "trial", "court", "and", "such", "a", "report", "be", "file", "and", "be", "hold", "in", "camera", "by", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "Now the record incidentally on that shows when we made a demand for it prior to trial and then again at trial, now the Court, page 81 of the record said, It is not a part of the record, it belongs to the Court itself and the Court will turn it over to you and you will be at liberty to read it as concerns any witnesses testimony.", "start": 2383.462, "stop": 2408.345, "duration": 24.88, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "record", "incidentally", "on", "that", "show", "when", "we", "make", "a", "demand", "for", "it", "prior", "to", "trial", "and", "then", "again", "at", "trial", "now", "the", "court", "page", "of", "the", "record", "say", "it", "be", "not", "a", "part", "of", "the", "record", "it", "belong", "to", "the", "court", "itself", "and", "the", "court", "will", "turn", "it", "over", "to", "you", "and", "you", "will", "be", "at", "liberty", "to", "read", "it", "as", "concern", "any", "witness", "testimony"]]}, {"text": "The Court wants to get at the truth or falsity at the proceeding so I will turn it over to you and you may use it for cross-examination.", "start": 2408.345, "stop": 2416.737, "duration": 8.39, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "want", "to", "get", "at", "the", "truth", "or", "falsity", "at", "the", "proceeding", "so", "i", "will", "turn", "it", "over", "to", "you", "and", "you", "may", "use", "it", "for", "cross", "examination"]]}, {"text": "And it was, portions of it were turned over to me somewhat in Jenks style, that is where a witness took the stand who was referred to in the fink report then I was entitled to cross-examine there on the basis of that.", "start": 2416.737, "stop": 2430.602, "duration": 13.86, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "be", "portion", "of", "it", "we", "be", "turn", "over", "to", "me", "somewhat", "in", "jenks", "style", "that", "be", "where", "a", "witness", "take", "the", "stand", "who", "be", "refer", "to", "in", "the", "fink", "report", "then", "i", "be", "entitle", "to", "cross", "examine", "there", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "that"]]}, {"text": "But that was not the entire report.", "start": 2430.602, "stop": 2432.819, "duration": 2.22, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "be", "not", "the", "entire", "report"]]}, {"text": "There is no way that we can show it to the Court where -- there is no way that we can indicate to the Court whether or not we are prejudiced which was the grounds relied upon by the Illinois Supreme Court for denying us a relief in that -- in connection with this particular point but I submit to the Court that it was impossible under the circumstances here for us to get such a report to determine whether or not we had been prejudiced since the trial judge himself to which (Inaudible) significance, refused to give it to us and refused to put it in the record.", "start": 2432.819, "stop": 2466.108, "duration": 33.29, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "way", "that", "we", "can", "show", "it", "to", "the", "court", "where", "there", "be", "no", "way", "that", "we", "can", "indicate", "to", "the", "court", "whether", "or", "not", "we", "be", "prejudiced", "which", "be", "the", "ground", "rely", "upon", "by", "the", "illinois", "supreme", "court", "for", "deny", "us", "a", "relief", "in", "that", "in", "connection", "with", "this", "particular", "point", "but", "i", "submit", "to", "the", "court", "that", "it", "be", "impossible", "under", "the", "circumstance", "here", "for", "us", "to", "get", "such", "a", "report", "to", "determine", "whether", "or", "not", "we", "have", "be", "prejudice", "since", "the", "trial", "judge", "himself", "to", "which", "inaudible", "significance", "refuse", "to", "give", "it", "to", "us", "and", "refuse", "to", "put", "it", "in", "the", "record"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Was the contempt judgment based in whole or in part on that report?", "start": 2466.108, "stop": 2471.039, "duration": 4.93, "cleanText": [["be", "the", "contempt", "judgment", "base", "in", "whole", "or", "in", "part", "on", "that", "report"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "We cannot tell Mr. Justice Black.", "start": 2471.039, "stop": 2473.265, "duration": 2.23, "cleanText": [["we", "can", "not", "tell", "mr", "justice", "black"]]}, {"text": "We cannot tell.", "start": 2473.265, "stop": 2474.053, "duration": 0.79, "cleanText": [["we", "can", "not", "tell"]]}, {"text": "I do not know frankly what use was made of it.", "start": 2474.053, "stop": 2477.634, "duration": 3.58, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know", "frankly", "what", "use", "be", "make", "of", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "When was the complaint and contempt filed in relation to the filing of that report?", "start": 2477.634, "stop": 2486.748, "duration": 9.11, "cleanText": [["when", "be", "the", "complaint", "and", "contempt", "file", "in", "relation", "to", "the", "filing", "of", "that", "report"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Afterwards, it was filed by the state's attorney and there were series of them.", "start": 2486.748, "stop": 2492.665, "duration": 5.92, "cleanText": [["afterwards", "it", "be", "file", "by", "the", "state", "s", "attorney", "and", "there", "we", "be", "series", "of", "them"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "It was --", "start": 2492.665, "stop": 2492.809, "duration": 0.14, "cleanText": [["it", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "First --", "start": 2492.809, "stop": 2493.045, "duration": 0.24, "cleanText": [["first"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- filed by the state's attorney in the contempt case?", "start": 2493.045, "stop": 2496.86, "duration": 3.82, "cleanText": [["file", "by", "the", "state", "s", "attorney", "in", "the", "contempt", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes sir, that's represented by Mr. Hladis.", "start": 2496.86, "stop": 2500.305, "duration": 3.44, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir", "that", "be", "represent", "by", "mr", "hladis"]]}, {"text": "The -- after this petition to which I referred to before have been filed then and after the fink report have been filed then there was a petition filed by the state's attorney seeking to have the petitioner to show cause why it should not be held in contempt.", "start": 2500.305, "stop": 2520.711, "duration": 20.41, "cleanText": [["the", "after", "this", "petition", "to", "which", "i", "refer", "to", "before", "have", "be", "file", "then", "and", "after", "the", "fink", "report", "have", "be", "file", "then", "there", "be", "a", "petition", "file", "by", "the", "state", "s", "attorney", "seek", "to", "have", "the", "petitioner", "to", "show", "because", "why", "it", "should", "not", "be", "hold", "in", "contempt"]]}, {"text": "Thereafter, they filed an amended petition after that had been attacked and it was upon the amended petition that the trial ultimately was had.", "start": 2520.711, "stop": 2529.101, "duration": 8.39, "cleanText": [["thereafter", "they", "file", "an", "amend", "petition", "after", "that", "have", "be", "attack", "and", "it", "be", "upon", "the", "amend", "petition", "that", "the", "trial", "ultimately", "be", "have"]]}, {"text": "But in direct answer to Your Honor, the petitions relating to contempt were filed after the receipt of the so-called fink report.", "start": 2529.101, "stop": 2540.075, "duration": 10.97, "cleanText": [["but", "in", "direct", "answer", "to", "your", "honor", "the", "petition", "relate", "to", "contempt", "we", "be", "file", "after", "the", "receipt", "of", "the", "so", "called", "fink", "report"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Eben, this petitioner has not served any of his sentence yet, hasn't he?", "start": 2540.075, "stop": 2546.456, "duration": 6.38, "cleanText": [["mr", "eben", "this", "petitioner", "have", "not", "serve", "any", "of", "his", "sentence", "yet", "have", "not", "he"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "No sir, no Your Honor.", "start": 2546.456, "stop": 2548.129, "duration": 1.67, "cleanText": [["no", "sir", "no", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Does the Illinois procedure in a criminal contempt case permit an appeal from sentence?", "start": 2548.129, "stop": 2556.421, "duration": 8.29, "cleanText": [["do", "the", "illinois", "procedure", "in", "a", "criminal", "contempt", "case", "permit", "an", "appeal", "from", "sentence"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, yes, yes.", "start": 2556.421, "stop": 2557.729, "duration": 1.31, "cleanText": [["oh", "yes", "yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "So that the appellate court might have reduced this sentence on appeal from the sentence even though it left the finding of guilt undisturbed, might it?", "start": 2557.729, "stop": 2571.806, "duration": 14.08, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "the", "appellate", "court", "might", "have", "reduce", "this", "sentence", "on", "appeal", "from", "the", "sentence", "even", "though", "it", "leave", "the", "finding", "of", "guilt", "undisturbed", "might", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think that it might but not the appellate court but if you use it in a --", "start": 2571.806, "stop": 2575.822, "duration": 4.02, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "it", "might", "but", "not", "the", "appellate", "court", "but", "if", "you", "use", "it", "in", "a"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I mean your appellate court --", "start": 2575.822, "stop": 2577.456, "duration": 1.63, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "mean", "your", "appellate", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- particular sentence made by --", "start": 2577.456, "stop": 2579.062, "duration": 1.61, "cleanText": [["particular", "sentence", "make", "by"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Ordinarily I take it in Illinois as -- is generally the case, there's no appeal from a sentence in a criminal case.", "start": 2579.062, "stop": 2587.59, "duration": 8.53, "cleanText": [["ordinarily", "i", "take", "it", "in", "illinois", "as", "be", "generally", "the", "case", "there", "be", "no", "appeal", "from", "a", "sentence", "in", "a", "criminal", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Unless a constitutional question is involved.", "start": 2587.59, "stop": 2589.563, "duration": 1.97, "cleanText": [["unless", "a", "constitutional", "question", "be", "involve"]]}, {"text": "We went directly to the Supreme Court.", "start": 2589.563, "stop": 2591.033, "duration": 1.47, "cleanText": [["we", "go", "directly", "to", "the", "supreme", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes but otherwise, there's no appeal from the sentence to have the sentence modified or reduced even though the finding of guilt stands --", "start": 2591.033, "stop": 2599.183, "duration": 8.15, "cleanText": [["yes", "but", "otherwise", "there", "be", "no", "appeal", "from", "the", "sentence", "to", "have", "the", "sentence", "modify", "or", "reduce", "even", "though", "the", "finding", "of", "guilt", "stand"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right", "start": 2599.183, "stop": 2599.294, "duration": 0.11, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- in New York.", "start": 2599.294, "stop": 2599.844, "duration": 0.55, "cleanText": [["in", "new", "york"]]}, {"text": "That's right.", "start": 2599.844, "stop": 2600.782, "duration": 0.94, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}, {"text": "But that's not true in the criminal contempt case you could have appealed to have this sentence reduced even though the finding of guilt remain?", "start": 2600.782, "stop": 2608.953, "duration": 8.17, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "be", "not", "true", "in", "the", "criminal", "contempt", "case", "you", "could", "have", "appeal", "to", "have", "this", "sentence", "reduce", "even", "though", "the", "finding", "of", "guilt", "remain"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "I -- as a matter of fact Mr. Justice Brennan, I wrote a part of my brief in the Illinois Supreme Court on that point asking them to at least reduce the sentence to conform with this Court's decision in Cheff.", "start": 2608.953, "stop": 2620.397, "duration": 11.44, "cleanText": [["i", "as", "a", "matter", "of", "fact", "mr", "justice", "brennan", "i", "write", "a", "part", "of", "my", "brief", "in", "the", "illinois", "supreme", "court", "on", "that", "point", "ask", "them", "to", "at", "least", "reduce", "the", "sentence", "to", "conform", "with", "this", "court", "s", "decision", "in", "cheff"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "I see.", "start": 2620.397, "stop": 2621.365, "duration": 0.97, "cleanText": [["i", "see"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Although I'm not sure that my position is really too sound because in Cheff as I pointed out yesterday, you do have that Section 18, Title I defining petty crimes and we don't have anything like that in Illinois at all.", "start": 2621.365, "stop": 2635.818, "duration": 14.45, "cleanText": [["although", "I", "be", "not", "sure", "that", "my", "position", "be", "really", "too", "sound", "because", "in", "cheff", "as", "i", "point", "out", "yesterday", "you", "do", "have", "that", "section", "title", "i", "define", "petty", "crime", "and", "we", "do", "not", "have", "anything", "like", "that", "in", "illinois", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "A defense is either a misdemeanor or it's a felony.", "start": 2635.818, "stop": 2640.451, "duration": 4.63, "cleanText": [["a", "defense", "be", "either", "a", "misdemeanor", "or", "it", "be", "a", "felony"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, did you have any Illinois authorities in which an appellate court had reduced the criminal contempt sentence?", "start": 2640.451, "stop": 2649.123, "duration": 8.67, "cleanText": [["well", "do", "you", "have", "any", "illinois", "authority", "in", "which", "an", "appellate", "court", "have", "reduce", "the", "criminal", "contempt", "sentence"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "No sir.", "start": 2649.123, "stop": 2649.428, "duration": 0.3, "cleanText": [["no", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you have -- you don't have that?", "start": 2649.428, "stop": 2650.487, "duration": 1.06, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "have", "you", "do", "not", "have", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "No sir.", "start": 2650.487, "stop": 2652.293, "duration": 1.81, "cleanText": [["no", "sir"]]}, {"text": "In fact, I'm not sure that there are (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 2652.293, "stop": 2654.045, "duration": 1.75, "cleanText": [["in", "fact", "I", "be", "not", "sure", "that", "there", "be", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Did the Illinois Supreme Court address itself to that part of your brief?", "start": 2654.045, "stop": 2658.719, "duration": 4.67, "cleanText": [["do", "the", "illinois", "supreme", "court", "address", "itself", "to", "that", "part", "of", "your", "brief"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "They addressed itself to the question of the two-year sentence without considering the facet which Your Honors is now discussing.", "start": 2658.719, "stop": 2669.298, "duration": 10.58, "cleanText": [["they", "address", "itself", "to", "the", "question", "of", "the", "two", "year", "sentence", "without", "consider", "the", "facet", "which", "your", "honor", "be", "now", "discuss"]]}, {"text": "They discussed it in terms of Cheff and they said really that what a sentence is, it's not at all relevant to whether or not it should be a jury trial.", "start": 2669.298, "stop": 2681.84, "duration": 12.54, "cleanText": [["they", "discuss", "it", "in", "term", "of", "cheff", "and", "they", "say", "really", "that", "what", "a", "sentence", "be", "it", "be", "not", "at", "all", "relevant", "to", "whether", "or", "not", "it", "should", "be", "a", "jury", "trial"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "May I ask you if your case depends at all on your judgment on whether this Court decides the federal constitution was right to a trial by jury as by the Fourteenth Amendment been made applicable to the states?", "start": 2681.84, "stop": 2705.328, "duration": 23.49, "cleanText": [["may", "i", "ask", "you", "if", "your", "case", "depend", "at", "all", "on", "your", "judgment", "on", "whether", "this", "court", "decide", "the", "federal", "constitution", "be", "right", "to", "a", "trial", "by", "jury", "as", "by", "the", "fourteenth", "amendment", "be", "make", "applicable", "to", "the", "state"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 2705.328, "stop": 2706.639, "duration": 1.31, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "We believe that --", "start": 2706.639, "stop": 2708.414, "duration": 1.78, "cleanText": [["we", "believe", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Was it your case depend on a holding to that (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 2708.414, "stop": 2711.514, "duration": 3.1, "cleanText": [["be", "it", "your", "case", "depend", "on", "a", "hold", "to", "that", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm sorry Your Honor.", "start": 2711.514, "stop": 2712.664, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sorry", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Does your case depend on a holding to that effect here, your case?", "start": 2712.664, "stop": 2719.88, "duration": 7.22, "cleanText": [["do", "your", "case", "depend", "on", "a", "hold", "to", "that", "effect", "here", "your", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "My case depends upon if I understood Your Honor correctly, the application of the Fourteenth Amendment to state courts in a long line of decisions.", "start": 2719.88, "stop": 2731.664, "duration": 11.78, "cleanText": [["my", "case", "depend", "upon", "if", "i", "understand", "your", "honor", "correctly", "the", "application", "of", "the", "fourteenth", "amendment", "to", "state", "court", "in", "a", "long", "line", "of", "decision"]]}, {"text": "I think I counted 23 of this Court in the last few years as well as an application of recently written by the Court in which you for the first time so far as I know, reach out to define what criminal proceedings are for the purpose of imposing constitutional rights at the Bar Association disciplinary proceedings.", "start": 2731.664, "stop": 2757.117, "duration": 25.45, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "i", "count", "of", "this", "court", "in", "the", "last", "few", "year", "as", "well", "as", "an", "application", "of", "recently", "write", "by", "the", "court", "in", "which", "you", "for", "the", "first", "time", "so", "far", "as", "i", "know", "reach", "out", "to", "define", "what", "criminal", "proceeding", "be", "for", "the", "purpose", "of", "impose", "constitutional", "right", "at", "the", "bar", "association", "disciplinary", "proceeding"]]}, {"text": "The juvenile proceedings, the Colorado Sex Offenses if you remember which were regarded as civil there, I know its three or four others which you -- this Court now regards as criminal in the sense that they require the application of certain constitutional rights.", "start": 2757.117, "stop": 2774.037, "duration": 16.92, "cleanText": [["the", "juvenile", "proceeding", "the", "colorado", "sex", "offenses", "if", "you", "remember", "which", "we", "be", "regard", "as", "civil", "there", "i", "know", "its", "three", "or", "four", "others", "which", "you", "this", "court", "now", "regard", "as", "criminal", "in", "the", "sense", "that", "they", "require", "the", "application", "of", "certain", "constitutional", "right"]]}, {"text": "And I say of course if in a disbarment proceeding or even a proceeding where a man loses his license under a municipal ordinance which this Court has decided if that is to be considered criminal providing for the application of constitutional rights then certainly conduct which is labeled right at the name criminal contempt and which of itself constitutes the violation of the state statute is felony should certainly be considered a criminal proceeding.", "start": 2774.037, "stop": 2804.463, "duration": 30.43, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "say", "of", "course", "if", "in", "a", "disbarment", "proceeding", "or", "even", "a", "proceeding", "where", "a", "man", "lose", "his", "license", "under", "a", "municipal", "ordinance", "which", "this", "court", "have", "decide", "if", "that", "be", "to", "be", "consider", "criminal", "providing", "for", "the", "application", "of", "constitutional", "right", "then", "certainly", "conduct", "which", "be", "label", "right", "at", "the", "name", "criminal", "contempt", "and", "which", "of", "itself", "constitute", "the", "violation", "of", "the", "state", "statute", "be", "felony", "should", "certainly", "be", "consider", "a", "criminal", "proceeding"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "But the question I was asking was this, do we have to decide -- is your case so far as you have claimed a right to trial by jury is concerned dependent on whether the Fourteenth Amendment made the right to trial by jury in the federal courts applicable to the states.", "start": 2804.463, "stop": 2832.319, "duration": 27.86, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "question", "i", "be", "ask", "be", "this", "do", "we", "have", "to", "decide", "be", "your", "case", "so", "far", "as", "you", "have", "claim", "a", "right", "to", "trial", "by", "jury", "be", "concern", "dependent", "on", "whether", "the", "fourteenth", "amendment", "make", "the", "right", "to", "trial", "by", "jury", "in", "the", "federal", "court", "applicable", "to", "the", "state"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "My answer is to the affirmative.", "start": 2832.319, "stop": 2836.006, "duration": 3.69, "cleanText": [["my", "answer", "be", "to", "the", "affirmative"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "You say we do.", "start": 2836.006, "stop": 2839.4, "duration": 3.39, "cleanText": [["you", "say", "we", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm sorry.", "start": 2839.4, "stop": 2840.174, "duration": 0.77, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sorry"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "You say we do have to face that question?", "start": 2840.174, "stop": 2843.613, "duration": 3.44, "cleanText": [["you", "say", "we", "do", "have", "to", "face", "that", "question"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think that the Fourteenth Amendment is involved.", "start": 2843.613, "stop": 2846.859, "duration": 3.25, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "the", "fourteenth", "amendment", "be", "involve"]]}, {"text": "I have struggled with it and that has not yet occurred to by mind a way in which the problem could be treated without applying the constitutional inhibition to the states and the only way I think we could do that would be under the Fourteenth Amendment.", "start": 2846.859, "stop": 2865.225, "duration": 18.37, "cleanText": [["i", "have", "struggle", "with", "it", "and", "that", "have", "not", "yet", "occur", "to", "by", "mind", "a", "way", "in", "which", "the", "problem", "could", "be", "treat", "without", "apply", "the", "constitutional", "inhibition", "to", "the", "state", "and", "the", "only", "way", "i", "think", "we", "could", "do", "that", "would", "be", "under", "the", "fourteenth", "amendment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well there is -- is a -- there may be an alternative may there not and that is, does it, for this Court to consider whether a jury trial should have been made available in this particular type of criminal contempt in view of the fact that the state does -- has adapted a jury trial system and that that jury trial system would embrace the right to a jury trial if this -- if the petitioner here have been prosecuted for forgery under the criminal statute.", "start": 2865.225, "stop": 2908.184, "duration": 42.96, "cleanText": [["well", "there", "be", "be", "a", "there", "may", "be", "an", "alternative", "may", "there", "not", "and", "that", "be", "do", "it", "for", "this", "court", "to", "consider", "whether", "a", "jury", "trial", "should", "have", "be", "make", "available", "in", "this", "particular", "type", "of", "criminal", "contempt", "in", "view", "of", "the", "fact", "that", "the", "state", "do", "have", "adapt", "a", "jury", "trial", "system", "and", "that", "that", "jury", "trial", "system", "would", "embrace", "the", "right", "to", "a", "jury", "trial", "if", "this", "if", "the", "petitioner", "here", "have", "be", "prosecute", "for", "forgery", "under", "the", "criminal", "statute"]]}, {"text": "Now is it possible that that is an alternative theory to the one about which Mr. Justice Black was questioning you namely that the -- your -- that the jury trial provision in the Sixth Amendment does apply to the states by virtue of the Fourteenth Amendment.", "start": 2908.184, "stop": 2931.188, "duration": 23, "cleanText": [["now", "be", "it", "possible", "that", "that", "be", "an", "alternative", "theory", "to", "the", "one", "about", "which", "mr", "justice", "black", "be", "question", "you", "namely", "that", "the", "your", "that", "the", "jury", "trial", "provision", "in", "the", "sixth", "amendment", "do", "apply", "to", "the", "state", "by", "virtue", "of", "the", "fourteenth", "amendment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would certainly accept that as the alternative.", "start": 2931.188, "stop": 2935.876, "duration": 4.69, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "certainly", "accept", "that", "as", "the", "alternative"]]}, {"text": "If I understand Your Honor, I think you're referring to an interpretation of the Illinois constitution rather than the federal constitution would be, yes, I'll accept that.", "start": 2935.876, "stop": 2946.169, "duration": 10.29, "cleanText": [["if", "i", "understand", "your", "honor", "i", "think", "you", "be", "refer", "to", "an", "interpretation", "of", "the", "illinois", "constitution", "rather", "than", "the", "federal", "constitution", "would", "be", "yes", "I", "will", "accept", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Very well.", "start": 2946.169, "stop": 2946.744, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["very", "well"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony Bradley Eben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you very much.", "start": 2946.744, "stop": 2947.802, "duration": 1.06, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "very", "much"]]}]}]}], "decidedBy": "Warren Court", "arguedOn": "Jan  16 - 17, 1968", "petitioner": "Bloom", "respondent": "Illinois", "docket": "52", "citation": "391US194(1968)", "justiaLink": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/391/194", "lowerCourt": "", "grantedOn": "", "decidedOn": "May 20, 1968"}